var book = {
	"name": "2 Samuel",
	"numChapters": 24,
	"chapters": {
		"1": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">1 </span>After the death<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8024B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8024B\"></sup> of Saul, David returned from striking down<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8024C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8024C\"></sup> the Amalekites<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8024D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8024D\"></sup> and stayed in Ziklag two days.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>On the third day a man<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8025E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8025E\"></sup> arrived from Saul’s camp with his clothes torn and dust on his head.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8025F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8025F\"></sup> When he came to David, he fell<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8025G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8025G\"></sup> to the ground to pay him honor.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8025H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8025H\"></sup>",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>“Where have you come from?” David asked him.He answered, “I have escaped from the Israelite camp.”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>“What happened?” David asked. “Tell me.”“The men fled from the battle,” he replied. “Many of them fell and died. And Saul and his son Jonathan are dead.”",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Then David said to the young man who brought him the report, “How do you know that Saul and his son Jonathan are dead?”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>“I happened to be on Mount Gilboa,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8029I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8029I\"></sup>” the young man said, “and there was Saul, leaning on his spear, with the chariots and their drivers in hot pursuit.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>When he turned around and saw me, he called out to me, and I said, ‘What can I do?’",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>“He asked me, ‘Who are you?’“‘An Amalekite,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8031J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8031J\"></sup>’ I answered.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>“Then he said to me, ‘Stand here by me and kill me!<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8032K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8032K\"></sup> I’m in the throes of death, but I’m still alive.’",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>“So I stood beside him and killed him, because I knew that after he had fallen he could not survive. And I took the crown<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8033L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8033L\"></sup> that was on his head and the band on his arm and have brought them here to my lord.”",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Then David and all the men with him took hold of their clothes and tore<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8034M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8034M\"></sup> them.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>They mourned and wept and fasted till evening for Saul and his son Jonathan, and for the army of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and for the nation of Israel, because they had fallen by the sword.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>David said to the young man who brought him the report, “Where are you from?”“I am the son of a foreigner, an Amalekite,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8036N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8036N\"></sup>” he answered.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>David asked him, “Why weren’t you afraid to lift your hand to destroy the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>’s anointed?<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8037O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8037O\"></sup>”",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Then David called one of his men and said, “Go, strike him down!”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8038P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8038P\"></sup> So he struck him down, and he died.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8038Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8038Q\"></sup>",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>For David had said to him, “Your blood be on your own head.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8039R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8039R\"></sup> Your own mouth testified against you when you said, ‘I killed the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>’s anointed.’”",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>David took up this lament<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8040S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8040S\"></sup> concerning Saul and his son Jonathan,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8040T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8040T\"></sup>",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>and he ordered that the people of Judah be taught this lament of the bow (it is written in the Book of Jashar):<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8041U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8041U\"></sup>",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>“A gazelle lies slain on your heights, Israel.How the mighty<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8042V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8042V\"></sup> have fallen!<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8042W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8042W\"></sup>",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>“Tell it not in Gath,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8043X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8043X\"></sup>proclaim it not in the streets of Ashkelon,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8043Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8043Y\"></sup>lest the daughters of the Philistines<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8043Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8043Z\"></sup> be glad,lest the daughters of the uncircumcised rejoice.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8043AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8043AA\"></sup>",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>“Mountains of Gilboa,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8044AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8044AB\"></sup>may you have neither dew<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8044AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8044AC\"></sup> nor rain,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8044AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8044AD\"></sup>may no showers fall on your terraced fields.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8044AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8044AE\"></sup>For there the shield of the mighty was despised,the shield of Saul—no longer rubbed with oil.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8044AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8044AF\"></sup>",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>“From the blood<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8045AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8045AG\"></sup> of the slain,from the flesh of the mighty,the bow<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8045AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8045AH\"></sup> of Jonathan did not turn back,the sword of Saul did not return unsatisfied.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Saul and Jonathan—in life they were loved and admired,and in death they were not parted.They were swifter than eagles,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8046AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8046AI\"></sup>they were stronger than lions.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8046AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8046AJ\"></sup>",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>“Daughters of Israel,weep for Saul,who clothed you in scarlet and finery,who adorned your garments with ornaments of gold.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8047AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8047AK\"></sup>",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>“How the mighty have fallen in battle!Jonathan lies slain on your heights.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>I grieve<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8049AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8049AL\"></sup> for you, Jonathan<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8049AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8049AM\"></sup> my brother;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8049AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8049AN\"></sup>you were very dear to me.Your love for me was wonderful,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8049AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8049AO\"></sup>more wonderful than that of women.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>“How the mighty have fallen!The weapons of war have perished!”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8050AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8050AP\"></sup>"
		},
		"2": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">2 </span>In the course of time, David inquired<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8051A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8051A\"></sup> of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>. “Shall I go up to one of the towns of Judah?” he asked.The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said, “Go up.”David asked, “Where shall I go?”“To Hebron,”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8051B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8051B\"></sup> the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> answered.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>So David went up there with his two wives,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8052C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8052C\"></sup> Ahinoam of Jezreel and Abigail,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8052D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8052D\"></sup> the widow of Nabal of Carmel.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>David also took the men who were with him,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8053E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8053E\"></sup> each with his family, and they settled in Hebron<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8053F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8053F\"></sup> and its towns.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Then the men of Judah came to Hebron,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8054G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8054G\"></sup> and there they anointed<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8054H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8054H\"></sup> David king over the tribe of Judah.When David was told that it was the men from Jabesh Gilead<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8054I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8054I\"></sup> who had buried Saul,",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>he sent messengers to them to say to them, “The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> bless<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8055J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8055J\"></sup> you for showing this kindness to Saul your master by burying him.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>May the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> now show you kindness and faithfulness,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8056K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8056K\"></sup> and I too will show you the same favor because you have done this.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Now then, be strong<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8057L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8057L\"></sup> and brave, for Saul your master is dead, and the people of Judah have anointed me king over them.”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Meanwhile, Abner<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8058N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8058N\"></sup> son of Ner, the commander of Saul’s army, had taken Ish-Bosheth<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8058O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8058O\"></sup> son of Saul and brought him over to Mahanaim.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8058P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8058P\"></sup>",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>He made him king over Gilead,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8059Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8059Q\"></sup> Ashuri<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8059R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8059R\"></sup> and Jezreel, and also over Ephraim, Benjamin and all Israel.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8059S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8059S\"></sup>",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Ish-Bosheth son of Saul was forty years old when he became king over Israel, and he reigned two years. The tribe of Judah, however, remained loyal to David.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>The length of time David was king in Hebron over Judah was seven years and six months.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8061T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8061T\"></sup>",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Abner son of Ner, together with the men of Ish-Bosheth son of Saul, left Mahanaim and went to Gibeon.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8062U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8062U\"></sup>",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Joab<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8063V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8063V\"></sup> son of Zeruiah and David’s men went out and met them at the pool of Gibeon. One group sat down on one side of the pool and one group on the other side.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Then Abner said to Joab, “Let’s have some of the young men get up and fight hand to hand in front of us.”“All right, let them do it,” Joab said.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>So they stood up and were counted off—twelve men for Benjamin and Ish-Bosheth son of Saul, and twelve for David.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Then each man grabbed his opponent by the head and thrust his dagger<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8066W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8066W\"></sup> into his opponent’s side, and they fell down together. So that place in Gibeon was called Helkath Hazzurim.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>The battle that day was very fierce, and Abner and the Israelites were defeated<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8067X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8067X\"></sup> by David’s men.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8067Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8067Y\"></sup>",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>The three sons of Zeruiah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8068Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8068Z\"></sup> were there: Joab,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8068AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8068AA\"></sup> Abishai<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8068AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8068AB\"></sup> and Asahel.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8068AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8068AC\"></sup> Now Asahel was as fleet-footed as a wild gazelle.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8068AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8068AD\"></sup>",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>He chased Abner, turning neither to the right nor to the left as he pursued him.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Abner looked behind him and asked, “Is that you, Asahel?”“It is,” he answered.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Then Abner said to him, “Turn aside to the right or to the left; take on one of the young men and strip him of his weapons.” But Asahel would not stop chasing him.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Again Abner warned Asahel, “Stop chasing me! Why should I strike you down? How could I look your brother Joab in the face?”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8072AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8072AE\"></sup>",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>But Asahel refused to give up the pursuit; so Abner thrust the butt of his spear into Asahel’s stomach,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8073AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8073AF\"></sup> and the spear came out through his back. He fell there and died on the spot. And every man stopped when he came to the place where Asahel had fallen and died.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8073AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8073AG\"></sup>",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>But Joab and Abishai pursued Abner, and as the sun was setting, they came to the hill of Ammah, near Giah on the way to the wasteland of Gibeon.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Then the men of Benjamin rallied behind Abner. They formed themselves into a group and took their stand on top of a hill.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Abner called out to Joab, “Must the sword devour<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8076AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8076AH\"></sup> forever? Don’t you realize that this will end in bitterness? How long before you order your men to stop pursuing their fellow Israelites?”",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Joab answered, “As surely as God lives, if you had not spoken, the men would have continued pursuing them until morning.”",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>So Joab<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8078AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8078AI\"></sup> blew the trumpet,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8078AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8078AJ\"></sup> and all the troops came to a halt; they no longer pursued Israel, nor did they fight anymore.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>All that night Abner and his men marched through the Arabah.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8079AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8079AK\"></sup> They crossed the Jordan, continued through the morning hours and came to Mahanaim.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8079AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8079AL\"></sup>",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>Then Joab stopped pursuing Abner and assembled the whole army. Besides Asahel, nineteen of David’s men were found missing.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>But David’s men had killed three hundred and sixty Benjamites who were with Abner.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>They took Asahel and buried him in his father’s tomb<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8082AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8082AM\"></sup> at Bethlehem. Then Joab and his men marched all night and arrived at Hebron by daybreak."
		},
		"3": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">3 </span>The war between the house of Saul and the house of David lasted a long time.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8083A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8083A\"></sup> David grew stronger and stronger,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8083B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8083B\"></sup> while the house of Saul grew weaker and weaker.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8083C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8083C\"></sup>",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Sons were born to David in Hebron:His firstborn was Amnon<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8084D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8084D\"></sup> the son of Ahinoam<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8084E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8084E\"></sup> of Jezreel;",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>his second, Kileab the son of Abigail<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8085F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8085F\"></sup> the widow of Nabal of Carmel;the third, Absalom<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8085G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8085G\"></sup> the son of Maakah daughter of Talmai king of Geshur;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8085H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8085H\"></sup>",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>the fourth, Adonijah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8086I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8086I\"></sup> the son of Haggith;the fifth, Shephatiah the son of Abital;",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>and the sixth, Ithream the son of David’s wife Eglah.These were born to David in Hebron.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>During the war between the house of Saul and the house of David, Abner<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8088J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8088J\"></sup> had been strengthening his own position in the house of Saul.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Now Saul had had a concubine<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8089K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8089K\"></sup> named Rizpah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8089L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8089L\"></sup> daughter of Aiah. And Ish-Bosheth said to Abner, “Why did you sleep with my father’s concubine?”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Abner was very angry because of what Ish-Bosheth said. So he answered, “Am I a dog’s head<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8090M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8090M\"></sup>—on Judah’s side? This very day I am loyal to the house of your father Saul and to his family and friends. I haven’t handed you over to David. Yet now you accuse me of an offense involving this woman!",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>May God deal with Abner, be it ever so severely, if I do not do for David what the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> promised<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8091N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8091N\"></sup> him on oath",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>and transfer the kingdom from the house of Saul and establish David’s throne over Israel and Judah from Dan to Beersheba.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8092O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8092O\"></sup>",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Ish-Bosheth did not dare to say another word to Abner, because he was afraid of him.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Then Abner sent messengers on his behalf to say to David, “Whose land is it? Make an agreement with me, and I will help you bring all Israel over to you.”",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>“Good,” said David. “I will make an agreement with you. But I demand one thing of you: Do not come into my presence unless you bring Michal daughter of Saul when you come to see me.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8095P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8095P\"></sup>",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Then David sent messengers to Ish-Bosheth son of Saul, demanding, “Give me my wife Michal,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8096Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8096Q\"></sup> whom I betrothed to myself for the price of a hundred Philistine foreskins.”",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>So Ish-Bosheth gave orders and had her taken away from her husband<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8097R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8097R\"></sup> Paltiel<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8097S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8097S\"></sup> son of Laish.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Her husband, however, went with her, weeping behind her all the way to Bahurim.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8098T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8098T\"></sup> Then Abner said to him, “Go back home!” So he went back.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Abner conferred with the elders<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8099U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8099U\"></sup> of Israel and said, “For some time you have wanted to make David your king.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Now do it! For the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> promised David, ‘By my servant David I will rescue my people Israel from the hand of the Philistines<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8100V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8100V\"></sup> and from the hand of all their enemies.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8100W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8100W\"></sup>’”",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Abner also spoke to the Benjamites in person. Then he went to Hebron to tell David everything that Israel and the whole tribe of Benjamin<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8101X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8101X\"></sup> wanted to do.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>When Abner, who had twenty men with him, came to David at Hebron, David prepared a feast<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8102Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8102Y\"></sup> for him and his men.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Then Abner said to David, “Let me go at once and assemble all Israel for my lord the king, so that they may make a covenant<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8103Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8103Z\"></sup> with you, and that you may rule over all that your heart desires.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8103AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8103AA\"></sup> So David sent Abner away, and he went in peace.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Just then David’s men and Joab returned from a raid and brought with them a great deal of plunder. But Abner was no longer with David in Hebron, because David had sent him away, and he had gone in peace.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>When Joab and all the soldiers with him arrived, he was told that Abner son of Ner had come to the king and that the king had sent him away and that he had gone in peace.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>So Joab went to the king and said, “What have you done? Look, Abner came to you. Why did you let him go? Now he is gone!",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>You know Abner son of Ner; he came to deceive you and observe your movements and find out everything you are doing.”",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Joab then left David and sent messengers after Abner, and they brought him back from the cistern at Sirah. But David did not know it.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Now when Abner<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8109AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8109AB\"></sup> returned to Hebron, Joab took him aside into an inner chamber, as if to speak with him privately. And there, to avenge the blood of his brother Asahel, Joab stabbed him<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8109AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8109AC\"></sup> in the stomach, and he died.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8109AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8109AD\"></sup>",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Later, when David heard about this, he said, “I and my kingdom are forever innocent<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8110AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8110AE\"></sup> before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> concerning the blood of Abner son of Ner.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>May his blood<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8111AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8111AF\"></sup> fall on the head of Joab and on his whole family!<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8111AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8111AG\"></sup> May Joab’s family never be without someone who has a running sore<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8111AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8111AH\"></sup> or leprosy or who leans on a crutch or who falls by the sword or who lacks food.”",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>(Joab and his brother Abishai murdered Abner because he had killed their brother Asahel in the battle at Gibeon.)",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>Then David said to Joab and all the people with him, “Tear your clothes and put on sackcloth<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8113AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8113AI\"></sup> and walk in mourning<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8113AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8113AJ\"></sup> in front of Abner.” King David himself walked behind the bier.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>They buried Abner in Hebron, and the king wept<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8114AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8114AK\"></sup> aloud at Abner’s tomb. All the people wept also.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>The king sang this lament<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8115AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8115AL\"></sup> for Abner:“Should Abner have died as the lawless die?",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup><span class=\"indent-1-breaks\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span>Your hands were not bound,your feet were not fettered.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8116AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8116AM\"></sup>You fell as one falls before the wicked.”And all the people wept over him again.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>Then they all came and urged David to eat something while it was still day; but David took an oath, saying, “May God deal with me, be it ever so severely,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8117AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8117AN\"></sup> if I taste bread<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8117AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8117AO\"></sup> or anything else before the sun sets!”",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>All the people took note and were pleased; indeed, everything the king did pleased them.",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>So on that day all the people there and all Israel knew that the king had no part<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8119AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8119AP\"></sup> in the murder of Abner son of Ner.",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>Then the king said to his men, “Do you not realize that a commander and a great man has fallen<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8120AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8120AQ\"></sup> in Israel this day?",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>And today, though I am the anointed king, I am weak, and these sons of Zeruiah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8121AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8121AR\"></sup> are too strong<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8121AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8121AS\"></sup> for me.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8121AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8121AT\"></sup> May the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> repay<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8121AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8121AU\"></sup> the evildoer according to his evil deeds!”"
		},
		"4": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">4 </span>When Ish-Bosheth son of Saul heard that Abner<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8122A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8122A\"></sup> had died in Hebron, he lost courage, and all Israel became alarmed.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Now Saul’s son had two men who were leaders of raiding bands. One was named Baanah and the other Rekab; they were sons of Rimmon the Beerothite from the tribe of Benjamin—Beeroth<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8123B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8123B\"></sup> is considered part of Benjamin,",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>because the people of Beeroth fled to Gittaim<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8124C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8124C\"></sup> and have resided there as foreigners to this day.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>(Jonathan<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8125D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8125D\"></sup> son of Saul had a son who was lame in both feet. He was five years old when the news<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8125E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8125E\"></sup> about Saul and Jonathan came from Jezreel. His nurse picked him up and fled, but as she hurried to leave, he fell and became disabled.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8125F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8125F\"></sup> His name was Mephibosheth.)<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8125G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8125G\"></sup>",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Now Rekab and Baanah, the sons of Rimmon the Beerothite, set out for the house of Ish-Bosheth,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8126H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8126H\"></sup> and they arrived there in the heat of the day while he was taking his noonday rest.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8126I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8126I\"></sup>",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>They went into the inner part of the house as if to get some wheat, and they stabbed<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8127J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8127J\"></sup> him in the stomach. Then Rekab and his brother Baanah slipped away.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>They had gone into the house while he was lying on the bed in his bedroom. After they stabbed and killed him, they cut off his head. Taking it with them, they traveled all night by way of the Arabah.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8128K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8128K\"></sup>",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>They brought the head<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8129L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8129L\"></sup> of Ish-Bosheth to David at Hebron and said to the king, “Here is the head of Ish-Bosheth son of Saul,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8129M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8129M\"></sup> your enemy, who tried to kill you. This day the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has avenged<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8129N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8129N\"></sup> my lord the king against Saul and his offspring.”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>David answered Rekab and his brother Baanah, the sons of Rimmon the Beerothite, “As surely as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> lives, who has delivered<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8130O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8130O\"></sup> me out of every trouble,",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>when someone told me, ‘Saul is dead,’ and thought he was bringing good news, I seized him and put him to death in Ziklag.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8131P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8131P\"></sup> That was the reward I gave him for his news!",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>How much more—when wicked men have killed an innocent man in his own house and on his own bed—should I not now demand his blood<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8132Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8132Q\"></sup> from your hand and rid the earth of you!”",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>So David gave an order to his men, and they killed them.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8133R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8133R\"></sup> They cut off their hands and feet and hung the bodies by the pool in Hebron. But they took the head of Ish-Bosheth and buried it in Abner’s tomb at Hebron."
		},
		"5": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">5 </span>All the tribes of Israel<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8134B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8134B\"></sup> came to David at Hebron and said, “We are your own flesh and blood.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8134C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8134C\"></sup>",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>In the past, while Saul was king over us, you were the one who led Israel on their military campaigns.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8135D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8135D\"></sup> And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8135E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8135E\"></sup> to you, ‘You will shepherd<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8135F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8135F\"></sup> my people Israel, and you will become their ruler.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8135G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8135G\"></sup>’”",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>When all the elders of Israel had come to King David at Hebron, the king made a covenant<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8136H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8136H\"></sup> with them at Hebron before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and they anointed<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8136I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8136I\"></sup> David king over Israel.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>David was thirty years old<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8137J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8137J\"></sup> when he became king, and he reigned<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8137K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8137K\"></sup> forty<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8137L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8137L\"></sup> years.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>In Hebron he reigned over Judah seven years and six months,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8138M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8138M\"></sup> and in Jerusalem he reigned over all Israel and Judah thirty-three years.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>The king and his men marched to Jerusalem<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8139P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8139P\"></sup> to attack the Jebusites,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8139Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8139Q\"></sup> who lived there. The Jebusites said to David, “You will not get in here; even the blind and the lame can ward you off.” They thought, “David cannot get in here.”",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Nevertheless, David captured the fortress of Zion<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8140R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8140R\"></sup>—which is the City of David.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8140S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8140S\"></sup>",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>On that day David had said, “Anyone who conquers the Jebusites will have to use the water shaft<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8141T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8141T\"></sup> to reach those ‘lame and blind’<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8141U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8141U\"></sup> who are David’s enemies.” That is why they say, “The ‘blind and lame’ will not enter the palace.”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>David then took up residence in the fortress and called it the City of David. He built up the area around it, from the terraces<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8142V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8142V\"></sup> inward.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>And he became more and more powerful,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8143W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8143W\"></sup> because the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> God Almighty<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8143X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8143X\"></sup> was with him.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8143Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8143Y\"></sup>",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Now Hiram<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8144Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8144Z\"></sup> king of Tyre sent envoys to David, along with cedar logs and carpenters and stonemasons, and they built a palace for David.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Then David knew that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had established him as king over Israel and had exalted his kingdom<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8145AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8145AA\"></sup> for the sake of his people Israel.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>After he left Hebron, David took more concubines and wives<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8146AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8146AB\"></sup> in Jerusalem, and more sons and daughters were born to him.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>These are the names of the children born to him there:<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8147AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8147AC\"></sup> Shammua, Shobab, Nathan,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8147AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8147AD\"></sup> Solomon,",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Ibhar, Elishua, Nepheg, Japhia,",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Elishama, Eliada and Eliphelet.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>When the Philistines heard that David had been anointed king over Israel, they went up in full force to search for him, but David heard about it and went down to the stronghold.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8150AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8150AF\"></sup>",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Now the Philistines had come and spread out in the Valley of Rephaim;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8151AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8151AG\"></sup>",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>so David inquired<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8152AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8152AH\"></sup> of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, “Shall I go and attack the Philistines? Will you deliver them into my hands?”The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> answered him, “Go, for I will surely deliver the Philistines into your hands.”",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>So David went to Baal Perazim, and there he defeated them. He said, “As waters break out, the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has broken out against my enemies before me.” So that place was called Baal Perazim.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8153AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8153AI\"></sup>",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>The Philistines abandoned their idols there, and David and his men carried them off.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8154AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8154AJ\"></sup>",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Once more the Philistines came up and spread out in the Valley of Rephaim;",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>so David inquired of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and he answered, “Do not go straight up, but circle around behind them and attack them in front of the poplar trees.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>As soon as you hear the sound<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8157AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8157AK\"></sup> of marching in the tops of the poplar trees, move quickly, because that will mean the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has gone out in front<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8157AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8157AL\"></sup> of you to strike the Philistine army.”",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>So David did as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> commanded him, and he struck down the Philistines<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8158AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8158AM\"></sup> all the way from Gibeon<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8158AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8158AN\"></sup> to Gezer.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8158AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8158AO\"></sup>"
		},
		"6": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">6 </span>David again brought together all the able young men of Israel—thirty thousand.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>He and all his men went to Baalah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8160C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8160C\"></sup> in Judah to bring up from there the ark<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8160D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8160D\"></sup> of God, which is called by the Name,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8160E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8160E\"></sup> the name of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> Almighty, who is enthroned<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8160F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8160F\"></sup> between the cherubim<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8160G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8160G\"></sup> on the ark.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>They set the ark of God on a new cart<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8161H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8161H\"></sup> and brought it from the house of Abinadab, which was on the hill.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8161I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8161I\"></sup> Uzzah and Ahio, sons of Abinadab, were guiding the new cart",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>with the ark of God on it, and Ahio was walking in front of it.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>David and all Israel were celebrating<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8163J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8163J\"></sup> with all their might before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, with castanets, harps, lyres, timbrels, sistrums and cymbals.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8163K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8163K\"></sup>",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>When they came to the threshing floor of Nakon, Uzzah reached out and took hold of<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8164L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8164L\"></sup> the ark of God, because the oxen stumbled.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>’s anger burned against Uzzah because of his irreverent act;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8165M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8165M\"></sup> therefore God struck him down,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8165N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8165N\"></sup> and he died there beside the ark of God.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Then David was angry because the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>’s wrath<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8166O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8166O\"></sup> had broken out against Uzzah, and to this day that place is called Perez Uzzah.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8166P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8166P\"></sup>",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>David was afraid of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> that day and said, “How<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8167Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8167Q\"></sup> can the ark of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> ever come to me?”",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>He was not willing to take the ark of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> to be with him in the City of David. Instead, he took it to the house of Obed-Edom<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8168R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8168R\"></sup> the Gittite.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>The ark of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> remained in the house of Obed-Edom the Gittite for three months, and the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> blessed him and his entire household.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8169S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8169S\"></sup>",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Now King David<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8170T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8170T\"></sup> was told, “The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has blessed the household of Obed-Edom and everything he has, because of the ark of God.” So David went to bring up the ark of God from the house of Obed-Edom to the City of David with rejoicing.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>When those who were carrying the ark of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had taken six steps, he sacrificed<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8171U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8171U\"></sup> a bull and a fattened calf.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Wearing a linen ephod,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8172V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8172V\"></sup> David was dancing<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8172W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8172W\"></sup> before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> with all his might,",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>while he and all Israel were bringing up the ark of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> with shouts<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8173X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8173X\"></sup> and the sound of trumpets.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8173Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8173Y\"></sup>",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>As the ark of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> was entering the City of David,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8174Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8174Z\"></sup> Michal<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8174AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8174AA\"></sup> daughter of Saul watched from a window. And when she saw King David leaping and dancing before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, she despised him in her heart.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>They brought the ark of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and set it in its place inside the tent that David had pitched for it,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8175AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8175AB\"></sup> and David sacrificed burnt offerings<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8175AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8175AC\"></sup> and fellowship offerings before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>After he had finished sacrificing<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8176AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8176AD\"></sup> the burnt offerings and fellowship offerings, he blessed<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8176AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8176AE\"></sup> the people in the name of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> Almighty.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Then he gave a loaf of bread, a cake of dates and a cake of raisins<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8177AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8177AF\"></sup> to each person in the whole crowd of Israelites, both men and women.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8177AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8177AG\"></sup> And all the people went to their homes.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>When David returned home to bless his household, Michal daughter of Saul came out to meet him and said, “How the king of Israel has distinguished himself today, going around half-naked<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8178AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8178AH\"></sup> in full view of the slave girls of his servants as any vulgar fellow would!”",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>David said to Michal, “It was before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, who chose me rather than your father or anyone from his house when he appointed<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8179AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8179AI\"></sup> me ruler<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8179AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8179AJ\"></sup> over the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>’s people Israel—I will celebrate before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>I will become even more undignified than this, and I will be humiliated in my own eyes. But by these slave girls you spoke of, I will be held in honor.”",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>And Michal daughter of Saul had no children to the day of her death."
		},
		"7": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">7 </span>After the king was settled in his palace<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8182B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8182B\"></sup> and the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had given him rest from all his enemies<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8182C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8182C\"></sup> around him,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8182D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8182D\"></sup>",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>he said to Nathan<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8183E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8183E\"></sup> the prophet, “Here I am, living in a house<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8183F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8183F\"></sup> of cedar, while the ark of God remains in a tent.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8183G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8183G\"></sup>",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Nathan replied to the king, “Whatever you have in mind,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8184H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8184H\"></sup> go ahead and do it, for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> is with you.”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>But that night the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> came to Nathan, saying:",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>“Go and tell my servant David, ‘This is what the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> says: Are you<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8186I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8186I\"></sup> the one to build me a house to dwell in?<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8186J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8186J\"></sup>",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>I have not dwelt in a house from the day I brought the Israelites up out of Egypt to this day.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8187K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8187K\"></sup> I have been moving from place to place with a tent<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8187L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8187L\"></sup> as my dwelling.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8187M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8187M\"></sup>",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Wherever I have moved with all the Israelites,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8188N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8188N\"></sup> did I ever say to any of their rulers whom I commanded to shepherd<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8188O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8188O\"></sup> my people Israel, “Why have you not built me a house<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8188P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8188P\"></sup> of cedar?<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8188Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8188Q\"></sup>”’",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>“Now then, tell my servant David, ‘This is what the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> Almighty says: I took you from the pasture, from tending the flock,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8189R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8189R\"></sup> and appointed you ruler<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8189S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8189S\"></sup> over my people Israel.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8189T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8189T\"></sup>",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>I have been with you wherever you have gone,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8190U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8190U\"></sup> and I have cut off all your enemies from before you.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8190V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8190V\"></sup> Now I will make your name great, like the names of the greatest men on earth.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8190W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8190W\"></sup>",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>And I will provide a place for my people Israel and will plant<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8191X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8191X\"></sup> them so that they can have a home of their own and no longer be disturbed.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8191Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8191Y\"></sup> Wicked<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8191Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8191Z\"></sup> people will not oppress them anymore,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8191AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8191AA\"></sup> as they did at the beginning",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>and have done ever since the time I appointed leaders<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8192AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8192AB\"></sup> over my people Israel. I will also give you rest from all your enemies.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8192AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8192AC\"></sup>“‘The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> declares<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8192AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8192AD\"></sup> to you that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> himself will establish<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8192AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8192AE\"></sup> a house<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8192AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8192AF\"></sup> for you:",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>When your days are over and you rest<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8193AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8193AG\"></sup> with your ancestors, I will raise up your offspring to succeed you, your own flesh and blood,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8193AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8193AH\"></sup> and I will establish his kingdom.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8193AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8193AI\"></sup>",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>He is the one who will build a house<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8194AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8194AJ\"></sup> for my Name,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8194AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8194AK\"></sup> and I will establish the throne of his kingdom forever.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8194AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8194AL\"></sup>",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>I will be his father, and he will be my son.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8195AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8195AM\"></sup> When he does wrong, I will punish him<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8195AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8195AN\"></sup> with a rod<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8195AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8195AO\"></sup> wielded by men, with floggings inflicted by human hands.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>But my love will never be taken away from him,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8196AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8196AP\"></sup> as I took it away from Saul,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8196AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8196AQ\"></sup> whom I removed from before you.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Your house and your kingdom will endure forever before me; your throne<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8197AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8197AR\"></sup> will be established<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8197AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8197AS\"></sup> forever.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8197AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8197AT\"></sup>’”",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Nathan reported to David all the words of this entire revelation.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Then King David went in and sat before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and he said:“Who am I,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8199AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8199AV\"></sup> Sovereign <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and what is my family, that you have brought me this far?",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>And as if this were not enough in your sight, Sovereign <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, you have also spoken about the future of the house of your servant—and this decree,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8200AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8200AW\"></sup> Sovereign <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, is for a mere human!",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>“What more can David say<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8201AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8201AX\"></sup> to you? For you know<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8201AY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AY&quot;&gt;AY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8201AY\"></sup> your servant,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8201AZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AZ&quot;&gt;AZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8201AZ\"></sup> Sovereign <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>For the sake of your word and according to your will, you have done this great thing and made it known to your servant.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>“How great<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8203BA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BA&quot;&gt;BA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8203BA\"></sup> you are,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8203BB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BB&quot;&gt;BB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8203BB\"></sup> Sovereign <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>! There is no one like<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8203BC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BC&quot;&gt;BC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8203BC\"></sup> you, and there is no God<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8203BD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BD&quot;&gt;BD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8203BD\"></sup> but you, as we have heard with our own ears.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8203BE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BE&quot;&gt;BE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8203BE\"></sup>",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>And who is like your people Israel<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8204BF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BF&quot;&gt;BF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8204BF\"></sup>—the one nation on earth that God went out to redeem as a people for himself, and to make a name<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8204BG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BG&quot;&gt;BG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8204BG\"></sup> for himself, and to perform great and awesome wonders<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8204BH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BH&quot;&gt;BH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8204BH\"></sup> by driving out nations and their gods from before your people, whom you redeemed<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8204BI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BI&quot;&gt;BI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8204BI\"></sup> from Egypt?",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>You have established your people Israel as your very own<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8205BJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BJ&quot;&gt;BJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8205BJ\"></sup> forever, and you, <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, have become their God.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8205BK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BK&quot;&gt;BK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8205BK\"></sup>",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>“And now, <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> God, keep forever the promise<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8206BL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BL&quot;&gt;BL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8206BL\"></sup> you have made concerning your servant and his house. Do as you promised,",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>so that your name<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8207BM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BM&quot;&gt;BM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8207BM\"></sup> will be great forever. Then people will say, ‘The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> Almighty is God over Israel!’ And the house of your servant David will be established<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8207BN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BN&quot;&gt;BN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8207BN\"></sup> in your sight.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>“<span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> Almighty, God of Israel, you have revealed this to your servant, saying, ‘I will build a house for you.’ So your servant has found courage to pray this prayer to you.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Sovereign <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, you are God! Your covenant is trustworthy,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8209BO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BO&quot;&gt;BO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8209BO\"></sup> and you have promised these good things to your servant.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>Now be pleased to bless the house of your servant, that it may continue forever in your sight; for you, Sovereign <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, have spoken, and with your blessing<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8210BP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BP&quot;&gt;BP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8210BP\"></sup> the house of your servant will be blessed forever.”"
		},
		"8": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">8 </span>In the course of time, David defeated the Philistines<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8211B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8211B\"></sup> and subdued<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8211C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8211C\"></sup> them, and he took Metheg Ammah from the control of the Philistines.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>David also defeated the Moabites.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8212D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8212D\"></sup> He made them lie down on the ground and measured them off with a length of cord. Every two lengths of them were put to death, and the third length was allowed to live. So the Moabites became subject to David and brought him tribute.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8212E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8212E\"></sup>",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Moreover, David defeated Hadadezer<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8213F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8213F\"></sup> son of Rehob, king of Zobah,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8213G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8213G\"></sup> when he went to restore his monument at the Euphrates<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8213H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8213H\"></sup> River.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>David captured a thousand of his chariots, seven thousand charioteers and twenty thousand foot soldiers. He hamstrung<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8214I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8214I\"></sup> all but a hundred of the chariot horses.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>When the Arameans of Damascus<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8215J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8215J\"></sup> came to help Hadadezer king of Zobah, David struck down twenty-two thousand of them.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>He put garrisons<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8216K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8216K\"></sup> in the Aramean kingdom of Damascus, and the Arameans became subject<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8216L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8216L\"></sup> to him and brought tribute. The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> gave David victory wherever he went.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8216M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8216M\"></sup>",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>David took the gold shields<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8217N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8217N\"></sup> that belonged to the officers of Hadadezer and brought them to Jerusalem.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>From Tebah and Berothai,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8218O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8218O\"></sup> towns that belonged to Hadadezer, King David took a great quantity of bronze.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>When Tou king of Hamath<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8219P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8219P\"></sup> heard that David had defeated the entire army of Hadadezer,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8219Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8219Q\"></sup>",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>he sent his son Joram to King David to greet him and congratulate him on his victory in battle over Hadadezer, who had been at war with Tou. Joram brought with him articles of silver, of gold and of bronze.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>King David dedicated<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8221R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8221R\"></sup> these articles to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, as he had done with the silver and gold from all the nations he had subdued:",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Edom<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8222S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8222S\"></sup> and Moab,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8222T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8222T\"></sup> the Ammonites<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8222U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8222U\"></sup> and the Philistines,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8222V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8222V\"></sup> and Amalek.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8222W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8222W\"></sup> He also dedicated the plunder taken from Hadadezer son of Rehob, king of Zobah.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>And David became famous<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8223X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8223X\"></sup> after he returned from striking down eighteen thousand Edomites in the Valley of Salt.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8223Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8223Y\"></sup>",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>He put garrisons throughout Edom, and all the Edomites<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8224Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8224Z\"></sup> became subject to David.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8224AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8224AA\"></sup> The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> gave David victory<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8224AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8224AB\"></sup> wherever he went.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8224AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8224AC\"></sup>",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>David reigned over all Israel, doing what was just and right<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8225AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8225AE\"></sup> for all his people.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Joab<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8226AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8226AF\"></sup> son of Zeruiah was over the army; Jehoshaphat<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8226AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8226AG\"></sup> son of Ahilud was recorder;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8226AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8226AH\"></sup>",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Zadok<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8227AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8227AI\"></sup> son of Ahitub and Ahimelek son of Abiathar<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8227AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8227AJ\"></sup> were priests; Seraiah was secretary;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8227AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8227AK\"></sup>",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Benaiah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8228AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8228AL\"></sup> son of Jehoiada was over the Kerethites<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8228AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8228AM\"></sup> and Pelethites; and David’s sons were priests."
		},
		"9": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">9 </span>David asked, “Is there anyone still left of the house of Saul to whom I can show kindness for Jonathan’s sake?”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8229A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8229A\"></sup>",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Now there was a servant of Saul’s household named Ziba.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8230B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8230B\"></sup> They summoned him to appear before David, and the king said to him, “Are you Ziba?”“At your service,” he replied.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>The king asked, “Is there no one still alive from the house of Saul to whom I can show God’s kindness?”Ziba answered the king, “There is still a son of Jonathan;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8231C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8231C\"></sup> he is lame<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8231D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8231D\"></sup> in both feet.”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>“Where is he?” the king asked.Ziba answered, “He is at the house of Makir<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8232E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8232E\"></sup> son of Ammiel in Lo Debar.”",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>So King David had him brought from Lo Debar, from the house of Makir son of Ammiel.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>When Mephibosheth son of Jonathan, the son of Saul, came to David, he bowed down to pay him honor.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8234F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8234F\"></sup>David said, “Mephibosheth!”“At your service,” he replied.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>“Don’t be afraid,” David said to him, “for I will surely show you kindness for the sake of your father Jonathan.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8235G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8235G\"></sup> I will restore to you all the land that belonged to your grandfather Saul, and you will always eat at my table.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8235H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8235H\"></sup>”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Mephibosheth<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8236I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8236I\"></sup> bowed down and said, “What is your servant, that you should notice a dead dog<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8236J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8236J\"></sup> like me?”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Then the king summoned Ziba, Saul’s steward, and said to him, “I have given your master’s grandson everything that belonged to Saul and his family.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>You and your sons and your servants are to farm the land for him and bring in the crops, so that your master’s grandson<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8238K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8238K\"></sup> may be provided for. And Mephibosheth, grandson of your master, will always eat at my table.” (Now Ziba had fifteen sons and twenty servants.)",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Then Ziba said to the king, “Your servant will do whatever my lord the king commands his servant to do.” So Mephibosheth ate at David’s table like one of the king’s sons.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8239L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8239L\"></sup>",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Mephibosheth had a young son named Mika, and all the members of Ziba’s household were servants of Mephibosheth.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8240M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8240M\"></sup>",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>And Mephibosheth lived in Jerusalem, because he always ate at the king’s table; he was lame in both feet."
		},
		"10": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">10 </span>In the course of time, the king of the Ammonites died, and his son Hanun succeeded him as king.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>David thought, “I will show kindness to Hanun son of Nahash,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8243B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8243B\"></sup> just as his father showed kindness to me.” So David sent a delegation to express his sympathy to Hanun concerning his father.When David’s men came to the land of the Ammonites,",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>the Ammonite commanders said to Hanun their lord, “Do you think David is honoring your father by sending envoys to you to express sympathy? Hasn’t David sent them to you only to explore the city and spy it out<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8244C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8244C\"></sup> and overthrow it?”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>So Hanun seized David’s envoys, shaved off half of each man’s beard,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8245D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8245D\"></sup> cut off their garments at the buttocks,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8245E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8245E\"></sup> and sent them away.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>When David was told about this, he sent messengers to meet the men, for they were greatly humiliated. The king said, “Stay at Jericho till your beards have grown, and then come back.”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>When the Ammonites realized that they had become obnoxious<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8247F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8247F\"></sup> to David, they hired twenty thousand Aramean<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8247G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8247G\"></sup> foot soldiers from Beth Rehob<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8247H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8247H\"></sup> and Zobah,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8247I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8247I\"></sup> as well as the king of Maakah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8247J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8247J\"></sup> with a thousand men, and also twelve thousand men from Tob.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8247K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8247K\"></sup>",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>On hearing this, David sent Joab<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8248L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8248L\"></sup> out with the entire army of fighting men.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>The Ammonites came out and drew up in battle formation at the entrance of their city gate, while the Arameans of Zobah and Rehob and the men of Tob and Maakah were by themselves in the open country.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Joab saw that there were battle lines in front of him and behind him; so he selected some of the best troops in Israel and deployed them against the Arameans.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>He put the rest of the men under the command of Abishai<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8251M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8251M\"></sup> his brother and deployed them against the Ammonites.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Joab said, “If the Arameans are too strong for me, then you are to come to my rescue; but if the Ammonites are too strong for you, then I will come to rescue you.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Be strong,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8253N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8253N\"></sup> and let us fight bravely for our people and the cities of our God. The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will do what is good in his sight.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8253O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8253O\"></sup>",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Then Joab and the troops with him advanced to fight the Arameans, and they fled before him.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>When the Ammonites<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8255P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8255P\"></sup> realized that the Arameans were fleeing, they fled before Abishai and went inside the city. So Joab returned from fighting the Ammonites and came to Jerusalem.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>After the Arameans saw that they had been routed by Israel, they regrouped.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Hadadezer had Arameans brought from beyond the Euphrates River; they went to Helam, with Shobak the commander of Hadadezer’s army leading them.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>When David was told of this, he gathered all Israel, crossed the Jordan and went to Helam. The Arameans formed their battle lines to meet David and fought against him.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>But they fled before Israel, and David killed seven hundred of their charioteers and forty thousand of their foot soldiers. He also struck down Shobak the commander of their army, and he died there.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>When all the kings who were vassals of Hadadezer saw that they had been routed by Israel, they made peace with the Israelites and became subject<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8260Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8260Q\"></sup> to them.So the Arameans<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8260R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8260R\"></sup> were afraid to help the Ammonites anymore."
		},
		"11": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">11 </span>In the spring,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8261A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8261A\"></sup> at the time when kings go off to war, David sent Joab<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8261B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8261B\"></sup> out with the king’s men and the whole Israelite army.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8261C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8261C\"></sup> They destroyed the Ammonites and besieged Rabbah.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8261D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8261D\"></sup> But David remained in Jerusalem.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>One evening David got up from his bed and walked around on the roof<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8262E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8262E\"></sup> of the palace. From the roof he saw<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8262F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8262F\"></sup> a woman bathing. The woman was very beautiful,",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>and David sent someone to find out about her. The man said, “She is Bathsheba,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8263G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8263G\"></sup> the daughter of Eliam<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8263H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8263H\"></sup> and the wife of Uriah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8263I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8263I\"></sup> the Hittite.”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Then David sent messengers to get her.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8264J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8264J\"></sup> She came to him, and he slept<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8264K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8264K\"></sup> with her. (Now she was purifying herself from her monthly uncleanness.)<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8264L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8264L\"></sup> Then she went back home.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>The woman conceived and sent word to David, saying, “I am pregnant.”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>So David sent this word to Joab: “Send me Uriah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8266M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8266M\"></sup> the Hittite.” And Joab sent him to David.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>When Uriah came to him, David asked him how Joab was, how the soldiers were and how the war was going.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Then David said to Uriah, “Go down to your house and wash your feet.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8268N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8268N\"></sup> So Uriah left the palace, and a gift from the king was sent after him.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>But Uriah slept at the entrance to the palace with all his master’s servants and did not go down to his house.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>David was told, “Uriah did not go home.” So he asked Uriah, “Haven’t you just come from a military campaign? Why didn’t you go home?”",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Uriah said to David, “The ark<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8271O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8271O\"></sup> and Israel and Judah are staying in tents, and my commander Joab and my lord’s men are camped in the open country. How could I go to my house to eat and drink and make love<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8271P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8271P\"></sup> to my wife? As surely as you live, I will not do such a thing!”",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Then David said to him, “Stay here one more day, and tomorrow I will send you back.” So Uriah remained in Jerusalem that day and the next.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>At David’s invitation, he ate and drank with him, and David made him drunk. But in the evening Uriah went out to sleep on his mat among his master’s servants; he did not go home.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>In the morning David wrote a letter<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8274Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8274Q\"></sup> to Joab and sent it with Uriah.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>In it he wrote, “Put Uriah out in front where the fighting is fiercest. Then withdraw from him so he will be struck down<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8275R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8275R\"></sup> and die.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8275S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8275S\"></sup>”",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>So while Joab had the city under siege, he put Uriah at a place where he knew the strongest defenders were.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>When the men of the city came out and fought against Joab, some of the men in David’s army fell; moreover, Uriah the Hittite died.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Joab sent David a full account of the battle.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>He instructed the messenger: “When you have finished giving the king this account of the battle,",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>the king’s anger may flare up, and he may ask you, ‘Why did you get so close to the city to fight? Didn’t you know they would shoot arrows from the wall?",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Who killed Abimelek<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8281T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8281T\"></sup> son of Jerub-Besheth? Didn’t a woman drop an upper millstone on him from the wall,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8281U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8281U\"></sup> so that he died in Thebez? Why did you get so close to the wall?’ If he asks you this, then say to him, ‘Moreover, your servant Uriah the Hittite is dead.’”",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>The messenger set out, and when he arrived he told David everything Joab had sent him to say.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>The messenger said to David, “The men overpowered us and came out against us in the open, but we drove them back to the entrance of the city gate.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Then the archers shot arrows at your servants from the wall, and some of the king’s men died. Moreover, your servant Uriah the Hittite is dead.”",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>David told the messenger, “Say this to Joab: ‘Don’t let this upset you; the sword devours one as well as another. Press the attack against the city and destroy it.’ Say this to encourage Joab.”",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>When Uriah’s wife heard that her husband was dead, she mourned for him.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>After the time of mourning<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8287V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8287V\"></sup> was over, David had her brought to his house, and she became his wife and bore him a son. But the thing David had done displeased<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8287W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8287W\"></sup> the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>."
		},
		"12": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">12 </span>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> sent Nathan<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8288B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8288B\"></sup> to David.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8288C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8288C\"></sup> When he came to him,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8288D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8288D\"></sup> he said, “There were two men in a certain town, one rich and the other poor.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>The rich man had a very large number of sheep and cattle,",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>but the poor man had nothing except one little ewe lamb he had bought. He raised it, and it grew up with him and his children. It shared his food, drank from his cup and even slept in his arms. It was like a daughter to him.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>“Now a traveler came to the rich man, but the rich man refrained from taking one of his own sheep or cattle to prepare a meal for the traveler who had come to him. Instead, he took the ewe lamb that belonged to the poor man and prepared it for the one who had come to him.”",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>David<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8292E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8292E\"></sup> burned with anger<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8292F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8292F\"></sup> against the man<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8292G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8292G\"></sup> and said to Nathan, “As surely as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> lives,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8292H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8292H\"></sup> the man who did this must die!",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>He must pay for that lamb four times over,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8293I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8293I\"></sup> because he did such a thing and had no pity.”",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Then Nathan said to David, “You are the man!<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8294J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8294J\"></sup> This is what the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Israel, says: ‘I anointed<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8294K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8294K\"></sup> you<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8294L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8294L\"></sup> king over Israel, and I delivered you from the hand of Saul.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>I gave your master’s house to you,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8295M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8295M\"></sup> and your master’s wives into your arms. I gave you all Israel and Judah. And if all this had been too little, I would have given you even more.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Why did you despise<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8296N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8296N\"></sup> the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> by doing what is evil in his eyes? You struck down<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8296O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8296O\"></sup> Uriah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8296P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8296P\"></sup> the Hittite with the sword and took his wife to be your own. You killed<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8296Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8296Q\"></sup> him with the sword of the Ammonites.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Now, therefore, the sword<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8297R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8297R\"></sup> will never depart from your house, because you despised me and took the wife of Uriah the Hittite to be your own.’",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>“This is what the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> says: ‘Out of your own household<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8298S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8298S\"></sup> I am going to bring calamity on you.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8298T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8298T\"></sup> Before your very eyes I will take your wives and give them to one who is close to you, and he will sleep with your wives in broad daylight.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8298U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8298U\"></sup>",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>You did it in secret,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8299V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8299V\"></sup> but I will do this thing in broad daylight<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8299W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8299W\"></sup> before all Israel.’”",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Then David said to Nathan, “I have sinned<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8300X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8300X\"></sup> against the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.”Nathan replied, “The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has taken away<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8300Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8300Y\"></sup> your sin.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8300Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8300Z\"></sup> You are not going to die.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8300AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8300AA\"></sup>",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>But because by doing this you have shown utter contempt for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8301AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8301AB\"></sup> the son born to you will die.”",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>After Nathan had gone home, the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> struck<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8302AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8302AC\"></sup> the child that Uriah’s wife had borne to David, and he became ill.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>David pleaded with God for the child. He fasted and spent the nights lying<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8303AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8303AD\"></sup> in sackcloth on the ground.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>The elders of his household stood beside him to get him up from the ground, but he refused,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8304AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8304AE\"></sup> and he would not eat any food with them.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8304AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8304AF\"></sup>",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>On the seventh day the child died. David’s attendants were afraid to tell him that the child was dead, for they thought, “While the child was still living, he wouldn’t listen to us when we spoke to him. How can we now tell him the child is dead? He may do something desperate.”",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>David noticed that his attendants were whispering among themselves, and he realized the child was dead. “Is the child dead?” he asked.“Yes,” they replied, “he is dead.”",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Then David got up from the ground. After he had washed,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8307AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8307AG\"></sup> put on lotions and changed his clothes,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8307AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8307AH\"></sup> he went into the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and worshiped. Then he went to his own house, and at his request they served him food, and he ate.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>His attendants asked him, “Why are you acting this way? While the child was alive, you fasted and wept,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8308AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8308AI\"></sup> but now that the child is dead, you get up and eat!”",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>He answered, “While the child was still alive, I fasted and wept. I thought, ‘Who knows?<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8309AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8309AJ\"></sup> The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> may be gracious to me and let the child live.’<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8309AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8309AK\"></sup>",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>But now that he is dead, why should I go on fasting? Can I bring him back again? I will go to him,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8310AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8310AL\"></sup> but he will not return to me.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8310AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8310AM\"></sup>",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Then David comforted his wife Bathsheba,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8311AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8311AN\"></sup> and he went to her and made love to her. She gave birth to a son, and they named him Solomon.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8311AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8311AO\"></sup> The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> loved him;",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>and because the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> loved him, he sent word through Nathan the prophet to name him Jedidiah.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8312AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8312AP\"></sup>",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Meanwhile Joab fought against Rabbah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8313AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8313AQ\"></sup> of the Ammonites and captured the royal citadel.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Joab then sent messengers to David, saying, “I have fought against Rabbah and taken its water supply.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Now muster the rest of the troops and besiege the city and capture it. Otherwise I will take the city, and it will be named after me.”",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>So David mustered the entire army and went to Rabbah, and attacked and captured it.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>David took the crown<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8317AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8317AR\"></sup> from their king’s head, and it was placed on his own head. It weighed a talent of gold, and it was set with precious stones. David took a great quantity of plunder from the city",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>and brought out the people who were there, consigning them to labor with saws and with iron picks and axes, and he made them work at brickmaking. David did this to all the Ammonite<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8318AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8318AS\"></sup> towns. Then he and his entire army returned to Jerusalem."
		},
		"13": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">13 </span>In the course of time, Amnon<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8319A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8319A\"></sup> son of David fell in love with Tamar,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8319B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8319B\"></sup> the beautiful sister of Absalom<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8319C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8319C\"></sup> son of David.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Amnon became so obsessed with his sister Tamar that he made himself ill. She was a virgin, and it seemed impossible for him to do anything to her.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Now Amnon had an adviser named Jonadab son of Shimeah,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8321D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8321D\"></sup> David’s brother. Jonadab was a very shrewd man.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>He asked Amnon, “Why do you, the king’s son, look so haggard morning after morning? Won’t you tell me?”Amnon said to him, “I’m in love with Tamar, my brother Absalom’s sister.”",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>“Go to bed and pretend to be ill,” Jonadab said. “When your father comes to see you, say to him, ‘I would like my sister Tamar to come and give me something to eat. Let her prepare the food in my sight so I may watch her and then eat it from her hand.’”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>So Amnon lay down and pretended to be ill. When the king came to see him, Amnon said to him, “I would like my sister Tamar to come and make some special bread in my sight, so I may eat from her hand.”",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>David sent word to Tamar at the palace: “Go to the house of your brother Amnon and prepare some food for him.”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>So Tamar went to the house of her brother Amnon, who was lying down. She took some dough, kneaded it, made the bread in his sight and baked it.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Then she took the pan and served him the bread, but he refused to eat.“Send everyone out of here,”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8327E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8327E\"></sup> Amnon said. So everyone left him.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Then Amnon said to Tamar, “Bring the food here into my bedroom so I may eat from your hand.” And Tamar took the bread she had prepared and brought it to her brother Amnon in his bedroom.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>But when she took it to him to eat, he grabbed<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8329F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8329F\"></sup> her and said, “Come to bed with me, my sister.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8329G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8329G\"></sup>",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>“No, my brother!” she said to him. “Don’t force me! Such a thing should not be done in Israel!<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8330H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8330H\"></sup> Don’t do this wicked thing.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8330I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8330I\"></sup>",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>What about me?<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8331J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8331J\"></sup> Where could I get rid of my disgrace? And what about you? You would be like one of the wicked fools in Israel. Please speak to the king; he will not keep me from being married to you.”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>But he refused to listen to her, and since he was stronger than she, he raped her.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8332K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8332K\"></sup>",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Then Amnon hated her with intense hatred. In fact, he hated her more than he had loved her. Amnon said to her, “Get up and get out!”",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>“No!” she said to him. “Sending me away would be a greater wrong than what you have already done to me.”But he refused to listen to her.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>He called his personal servant and said, “Get this woman out of my sight and bolt the door after her.”",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>So his servant put her out and bolted the door after her. She was wearing an ornate robe,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8336L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8336L\"></sup> for this was the kind of garment the virgin daughters of the king wore.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Tamar put ashes<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8337M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8337M\"></sup> on her head and tore the ornate robe she was wearing. She put her hands on her head and went away, weeping aloud as she went.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Her brother Absalom said to her, “Has that Amnon, your brother, been with you? Be quiet for now, my sister; he is your brother. Don’t take this thing to heart.” And Tamar lived in her brother Absalom’s house, a desolate woman.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>When King David heard all this, he was furious.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8339N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8339N\"></sup>",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>And Absalom never said a word to Amnon, either good or bad;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8340O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8340O\"></sup> he hated<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8340P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8340P\"></sup> Amnon because he had disgraced his sister Tamar.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Two years later, when Absalom’s sheepshearers<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8341Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8341Q\"></sup> were at Baal Hazor near the border of Ephraim, he invited all the king’s sons to come there.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Absalom went to the king and said, “Your servant has had shearers come. Will the king and his attendants please join me?”",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>“No, my son,” the king replied. “All of us should not go; we would only be a burden to you.” Although Absalom urged him, he still refused to go but gave him his blessing.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Then Absalom said, “If not, please let my brother Amnon come with us.”The king asked him, “Why should he go with you?”",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>But Absalom urged him, so he sent with him Amnon and the rest of the king’s sons.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Absalom<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8346R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8346R\"></sup> ordered his men, “Listen! When Amnon is in high<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8346S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8346S\"></sup> spirits from drinking wine and I say to you, ‘Strike Amnon down,’ then kill him. Don’t be afraid. Haven’t I given you this order? Be strong and brave.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8346T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8346T\"></sup>”",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>So Absalom’s men did to Amnon what Absalom had ordered. Then all the king’s sons got up, mounted their mules and fled.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>While they were on their way, the report came to David: “Absalom has struck down all the king’s sons; not one of them is left.”",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>The king stood up, tore<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8349U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8349U\"></sup> his clothes and lay down on the ground; and all his attendants stood by with their clothes torn.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>But Jonadab son of Shimeah, David’s brother, said, “My lord should not think that they killed all the princes; only Amnon is dead. This has been Absalom’s express intention ever since the day Amnon raped his sister Tamar.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>My lord the king should not be concerned about the report that all the king’s sons are dead. Only Amnon is dead.”",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>Meanwhile, Absalom had fled.Now the man standing watch looked up and saw many people on the road west of him, coming down the side of the hill. The watchman went and told the king, “I see men in the direction of Horonaim, on the side of the hill.”",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>Jonadab said to the king, “See, the king’s sons have come; it has happened just as your servant said.”",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>As he finished speaking, the king’s sons came in, wailing loudly. The king, too, and all his attendants wept very bitterly.",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>Absalom fled and went to Talmai<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8355V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8355V\"></sup> son of Ammihud, the king of Geshur. But King David mourned many days for his son.",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>After Absalom fled and went to Geshur, he stayed there three years.",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>And King David longed to go to Absalom,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8357W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8357W\"></sup> for he was consoled<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8357X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8357X\"></sup> concerning Amnon’s death."
		},
		"14": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">14 </span>Joab<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8358A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8358A\"></sup> son of Zeruiah knew that the king’s heart longed for Absalom.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>So Joab sent someone to Tekoa<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8359B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8359B\"></sup> and had a wise woman<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8359C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8359C\"></sup> brought from there. He said to her, “Pretend you are in mourning. Dress in mourning clothes, and don’t use any cosmetic lotions.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8359D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8359D\"></sup> Act like a woman who has spent many days grieving for the dead.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Then go to the king and speak these words to him.” And Joab<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8360E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8360E\"></sup> put the words in her mouth.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>When the woman from Tekoa went to the king, she fell with her face to the ground to pay him honor, and she said, “Help me, Your Majesty!”",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>The king asked her, “What is troubling you?”She said, “I am a widow; my husband is dead.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>I your servant had two sons. They got into a fight with each other in the field, and no one was there to separate them. One struck the other and killed him.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Now the whole clan has risen up against your servant; they say, ‘Hand over the one who struck his brother down, so that we may put him to death<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8364F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8364F\"></sup> for the life of his brother whom he killed; then we will get rid of the heir<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8364G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8364G\"></sup> as well.’ They would put out the only burning coal I have left,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8364H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8364H\"></sup> leaving my husband neither name nor descendant on the face of the earth.”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>The king said to the woman, “Go home,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8365I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8365I\"></sup> and I will issue an order in your behalf.”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>But the woman from Tekoa said to him, “Let my lord the king pardon<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8366J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8366J\"></sup> me and my family,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8366K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8366K\"></sup> and let the king and his throne be without guilt.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8366L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8366L\"></sup>”",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>The king replied, “If anyone says anything to you, bring them to me, and they will not bother you again.”",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>She said, “Then let the king invoke the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> his God to prevent the avenger<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8368M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8368M\"></sup> of blood from adding to the destruction, so that my son will not be destroyed.”“As surely as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> lives,” he said, “not one hair<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8368N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8368N\"></sup> of your son’s head will fall to the ground.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8368O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8368O\"></sup>”",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Then the woman said, “Let your servant speak a word to my lord the king.”“Speak,” he replied.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>The woman said, “Why then have you devised a thing like this against the people of God? When the king says this, does he not convict himself,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8370P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8370P\"></sup> for the king has not brought back his banished son?<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8370Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8370Q\"></sup>",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Like water<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8371R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8371R\"></sup> spilled on the ground, which cannot be recovered, so we must die.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8371S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8371S\"></sup> But that is not what God desires; rather, he devises ways so that a banished person<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8371T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8371T\"></sup> does not remain banished from him.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>“And now I have come to say this to my lord the king because the people have made me afraid. Your servant thought, ‘I will speak to the king; perhaps he will grant his servant’s request.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Perhaps the king will agree to deliver his servant from the hand of the man who is trying to cut off both me and my son from God’s inheritance.’<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8373U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8373U\"></sup>",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>“And now your servant says, ‘May the word of my lord the king secure my inheritance, for my lord the king is like an angel<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8374V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8374V\"></sup> of God in discerning<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8374W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8374W\"></sup> good and evil. May the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God be with you.’”",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Then the king said to the woman, “Don’t keep from me the answer to what I am going to ask you.”“Let my lord the king speak,” the woman said.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>The king asked, “Isn’t the hand of Joab<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8376X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8376X\"></sup> with you in all this?”The woman answered, “As surely as you live, my lord the king, no one can turn to the right or to the left from anything my lord the king says. Yes, it was your servant Joab who instructed me to do this and who put all these words into the mouth of your servant.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Your servant Joab did this to change the present situation. My lord has wisdom<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8377Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8377Y\"></sup> like that of an angel of God—he knows everything that happens in the land.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8377Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8377Z\"></sup>”",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>The king said to Joab, “Very well, I will do it. Go, bring back the young man Absalom.”",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Joab fell with his face to the ground to pay him honor, and he blessed the king.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8379AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8379AA\"></sup> Joab said, “Today your servant knows that he has found favor in your eyes, my lord the king, because the king has granted his servant’s request.”",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Then Joab went to Geshur and brought Absalom back to Jerusalem.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>But the king said, “He must go to his own house; he must not see my face.” So Absalom went to his own house and did not see the face of the king.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>In all Israel there was not a man so highly praised for his handsome appearance as Absalom. From the top of his head to the sole of his foot there was no blemish in him.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Whenever he cut the hair of his head<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8383AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8383AB\"></sup>—he used to cut his hair once a year because it became too heavy for him—he would weigh it, and its weight was two hundred shekels by the royal standard.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Three sons<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8384AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8384AC\"></sup> and a daughter were born to Absalom. His daughter’s name was Tamar,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8384AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8384AD\"></sup> and she became a beautiful woman.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Absalom lived two years in Jerusalem without seeing the king’s face.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>Then Absalom sent for Joab in order to send him to the king, but Joab refused to come to him. So he sent a second time, but he refused to come.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>Then he said to his servants, “Look, Joab’s field is next to mine, and he has barley<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8387AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8387AE\"></sup> there. Go and set it on fire.” So Absalom’s servants set the field on fire.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>Then Joab did go to Absalom’s house, and he said to him, “Why have your servants set my field on fire?<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8388AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8388AF\"></sup>”",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>Absalom said to Joab, “Look, I sent word to you and said, ‘Come here so I can send you to the king to ask, “Why have I come from Geshur?<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8389AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8389AG\"></sup> It would be better for me if I were still there!”’ Now then, I want to see the king’s face, and if I am guilty of anything, let him put me to death.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8389AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8389AH\"></sup>",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>So Joab went to the king and told him this. Then the king summoned Absalom, and he came in and bowed down with his face to the ground before the king. And the king kissed<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8390AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8390AI\"></sup> Absalom."
		},
		"15": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">15 </span>In the course of time,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8391A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8391A\"></sup> Absalom provided himself with a chariot<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8391B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8391B\"></sup> and horses and with fifty men to run ahead of him.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>He would get up early and stand by the side of the road leading to the city gate.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8392C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8392C\"></sup> Whenever anyone came with a complaint to be placed before the king for a decision, Absalom would call out to him, “What town are you from?” He would answer, “Your servant is from one of the tribes of Israel.”",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Then Absalom would say to him, “Look, your claims are valid and proper, but there is no representative of the king to hear you.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8393D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8393D\"></sup>",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>And Absalom would add, “If only I were appointed judge in the land!<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8394E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8394E\"></sup> Then everyone who has a complaint or case could come to me and I would see that they receive justice.”",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Also, whenever anyone approached him to bow down before him, Absalom would reach out his hand, take hold of him and kiss him.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Absalom behaved in this way toward all the Israelites who came to the king asking for justice, and so he stole the hearts<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8396F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8396F\"></sup> of the people of Israel.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>At the end of four years, Absalom said to the king, “Let me go to Hebron and fulfill a vow I made to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>While your servant was living at Geshur<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8398G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8398G\"></sup> in Aram, I made this vow:<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8398H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8398H\"></sup> ‘If the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> takes me back to Jerusalem, I will worship the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> in Hebron.’”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>The king said to him, “Go in peace.” So he went to Hebron.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Then Absalom sent secret messengers throughout the tribes of Israel to say, “As soon as you hear the sound of the trumpets,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8400I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8400I\"></sup> then say, ‘Absalom is king in Hebron.’”",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Two hundred men from Jerusalem had accompanied Absalom. They had been invited as guests and went quite innocently, knowing nothing about the matter.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>While Absalom was offering sacrifices, he also sent for Ahithophel<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8402J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8402J\"></sup> the Gilonite, David’s counselor,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8402K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8402K\"></sup> to come from Giloh,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8402L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8402L\"></sup> his hometown. And so the conspiracy gained strength, and Absalom’s following kept on increasing.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8402M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8402M\"></sup>",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>A messenger came and told David, “The hearts of the people of Israel are with Absalom.”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Then David said to all his officials who were with him in Jerusalem, “Come! We must flee,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8404N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8404N\"></sup> or none of us will escape from Absalom.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8404O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8404O\"></sup> We must leave immediately, or he will move quickly to overtake us and bring ruin on us and put the city to the sword.”",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>The king’s officials answered him, “Your servants are ready to do whatever our lord the king chooses.”",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>The king set out, with his entire household following him; but he left ten concubines<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8406P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8406P\"></sup> to take care of the palace.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>So the king set out, with all the people following him, and they halted at the edge of the city.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>All his men marched past him, along with all the Kerethites<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8408Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8408Q\"></sup> and Pelethites; and all the six hundred Gittites who had accompanied him from Gath marched before the king.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>The king said to Ittai<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8409R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8409R\"></sup> the Gittite, “Why should you come along with us? Go back and stay with King Absalom. You are a foreigner,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8409S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8409S\"></sup> an exile from your homeland.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>You came only yesterday. And today shall I make you wander<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8410T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8410T\"></sup> about with us, when I do not know where I am going? Go back, and take your people with you. May the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> show you kindness and faithfulness.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8410U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8410U\"></sup>",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>But Ittai replied to the king, “As surely as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> lives, and as my lord the king lives, wherever my lord the king may be, whether it means life or death, there will your servant be.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8411V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8411V\"></sup>",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>David said to Ittai, “Go ahead, march on.” So Ittai the Gittite marched on with all his men and the families that were with him.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>The whole countryside wept aloud<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8413W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8413W\"></sup> as all the people passed by. The king also crossed the Kidron Valley,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8413X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8413X\"></sup> and all the people moved on toward the wilderness.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Zadok<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8414Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8414Y\"></sup> was there, too, and all the Levites who were with him were carrying the ark<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8414Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8414Z\"></sup> of the covenant of God. They set down the ark of God, and Abiathar<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8414AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8414AA\"></sup> offered sacrifices until all the people had finished leaving the city.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Then the king said to Zadok, “Take the ark of God back into the city. If I find favor in the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>’s eyes, he will bring me back and let me see it and his dwelling place<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8415AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8415AB\"></sup> again.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>But if he says, ‘I am not pleased with you,’ then I am ready; let him do to me whatever seems good to him.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8416AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8416AC\"></sup>”",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>The king also said to Zadok the priest, “Do you understand?<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8417AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8417AD\"></sup> Go back to the city with my blessing. Take your son Ahimaaz with you, and also Abiathar’s son Jonathan.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8417AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8417AE\"></sup> You and Abiathar return with your two sons.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>I will wait at the fords<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8418AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8418AF\"></sup> in the wilderness until word comes from you to inform me.”",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>So Zadok and Abiathar took the ark of God back to Jerusalem and stayed there.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>But David continued up the Mount of Olives, weeping<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8420AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8420AG\"></sup> as he went; his head<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8420AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8420AH\"></sup> was covered and he was barefoot. All the people with him covered their heads too and were weeping as they went up.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>Now David had been told, “Ahithophel<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8421AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8421AI\"></sup> is among the conspirators with Absalom.” So David prayed, “<span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, turn Ahithophel’s counsel into foolishness.”",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>When David arrived at the summit, where people used to worship God, Hushai<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8422AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8422AJ\"></sup> the Arkite<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8422AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8422AK\"></sup> was there to meet him, his robe torn and dust<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8422AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8422AL\"></sup> on his head.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>David said to him, “If you go with me, you will be a burden<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8423AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8423AM\"></sup> to me.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>But if you return to the city and say to Absalom, ‘Your Majesty, I will be your servant; I was your father’s servant in the past, but now I will be your servant,’<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8424AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8424AN\"></sup> then you can help me by frustrating<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8424AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8424AO\"></sup> Ahithophel’s advice.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>Won’t the priests Zadok and Abiathar be there with you? Tell them anything you hear in the king’s palace.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8425AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8425AP\"></sup>",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>Their two sons, Ahimaaz<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8426AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8426AQ\"></sup> son of Zadok and Jonathan<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8426AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8426AR\"></sup> son of Abiathar, are there with them. Send them to me with anything you hear.”",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>So Hushai,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8427AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8427AS\"></sup> David’s confidant, arrived at Jerusalem as Absalom<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8427AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8427AT\"></sup> was entering the city."
		},
		"16": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">16 </span>When David had gone a short distance beyond the summit, there was Ziba,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8428A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8428A\"></sup> the steward of Mephibosheth, waiting to meet him. He had a string of donkeys saddled and loaded with two hundred loaves of bread, a hundred cakes of raisins, a hundred cakes of figs and a skin of wine.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8428B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8428B\"></sup>",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>The king asked Ziba, “Why have you brought these?”Ziba answered, “The donkeys are for the king’s household to ride on, the bread and fruit are for the men to eat, and the wine is to refresh<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8429C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8429C\"></sup> those who become exhausted in the wilderness.”",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>The king then asked, “Where is your master’s grandson?”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8430D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8430D\"></sup>Ziba<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8430E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8430E\"></sup> said to him, “He is staying in Jerusalem, because he thinks, ‘Today the Israelites will restore to me my grandfather’s kingdom.’”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Then the king said to Ziba, “All that belonged to Mephibosheth<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8431F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8431F\"></sup> is now yours.”“I humbly bow,” Ziba said. “May I find favor in your eyes, my lord the king.”",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>As King David approached Bahurim,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8432G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8432G\"></sup> a man from the same clan as Saul’s family came out from there. His name was Shimei<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8432H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8432H\"></sup> son of Gera, and he cursed<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8432I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8432I\"></sup> as he came out.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>He pelted David and all the king’s officials with stones, though all the troops and the special guard were on David’s right and left.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>As he cursed, Shimei said, “Get out, get out, you murderer, you scoundrel!",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has repaid you for all the blood you shed in the household of Saul, in whose place you have reigned.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8435J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8435J\"></sup> The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has given the kingdom into the hands of your son Absalom. You have come to ruin because you are a murderer!”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8435K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8435K\"></sup>",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Then Abishai<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8436L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8436L\"></sup> son of Zeruiah said to the king, “Why should this dead dog<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8436M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8436M\"></sup> curse my lord the king? Let me go over and cut off his head.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8436N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8436N\"></sup>",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>But the king said, “What does this have to do with you, you sons of Zeruiah?<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8437O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8437O\"></sup> If he is cursing because the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to him, ‘Curse David,’ who can ask, ‘Why do you do this?’”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8437P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8437P\"></sup>",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>David then said to Abishai and all his officials, “My son,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8438Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8438Q\"></sup> my own flesh and blood, is trying to kill me. How much more, then, this Benjamite! Leave him alone; let him curse, for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has told him to.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8438R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8438R\"></sup>",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>It may be that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will look upon my misery<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8439S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8439S\"></sup> and restore to me his covenant blessing<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8439T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8439T\"></sup> instead of his curse today.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8439U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8439U\"></sup>”",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>So David and his men continued along the road while Shimei was going along the hillside opposite him, cursing as he went and throwing stones at him and showering him with dirt.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>The king and all the people with him arrived at their destination exhausted.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8441V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8441V\"></sup> And there he refreshed himself.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Meanwhile, Absalom<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8442W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8442W\"></sup> and all the men of Israel came to Jerusalem, and Ahithophel<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8442X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8442X\"></sup> was with him.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Then Hushai<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8443Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8443Y\"></sup> the Arkite, David’s confidant, went to Absalom and said to him, “Long live the king! Long live the king!”",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Absalom said to Hushai, “So this is the love you show your friend? If he’s your friend, why didn’t you go with him?”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8444Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8444Z\"></sup>",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Hushai said to Absalom, “No, the one chosen by the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, by these people, and by all the men of Israel—his I will be, and I will remain with him.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Furthermore, whom should I serve? Should I not serve the son? Just as I served your father, so I will serve you.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8446AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8446AA\"></sup>",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Absalom said to Ahithophel, “Give us your advice. What should we do?”",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Ahithophel answered, “Sleep with your father’s concubines whom he left to take care of the palace. Then all Israel will hear that you have made yourself obnoxious to your father, and the hands of everyone with you will be more resolute.”",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>So they pitched a tent for Absalom on the roof, and he slept with his father’s concubines in the sight of all Israel.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8449AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8449AB\"></sup>",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Now in those days the advice<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8450AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8450AC\"></sup> Ahithophel gave was like that of one who inquires of God. That was how both David<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8450AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8450AD\"></sup> and Absalom regarded all of Ahithophel’s advice."
		},
		"17": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">17 </span>Ahithophel said to Absalom, “I would choose twelve thousand men and set out tonight in pursuit of David.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>I would attack him while he is weary and weak.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8452A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8452A\"></sup> I would strike him with terror, and then all the people with him will flee. I would strike down only the king<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8452B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8452B\"></sup>",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>and bring all the people back to you. The death of the man you seek will mean the return of all; all the people will be unharmed.”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>This plan seemed good to Absalom and to all the elders of Israel.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>But Absalom said, “Summon also Hushai<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8455C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8455C\"></sup> the Arkite, so we can hear what he has to say as well.”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>When Hushai came to him, Absalom said, “Ahithophel has given this advice. Should we do what he says? If not, give us your opinion.”",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Hushai replied to Absalom, “The advice Ahithophel has given is not good this time.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>You know your father and his men; they are fighters, and as fierce as a wild bear robbed of her cubs.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8458D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8458D\"></sup> Besides, your father is an experienced fighter;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8458E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8458E\"></sup> he will not spend the night with the troops.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Even now, he is hidden in a cave or some other place.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8459F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8459F\"></sup> If he should attack your troops first, whoever hears about it will say, ‘There has been a slaughter among the troops who follow Absalom.’",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Then even the bravest soldier, whose heart is like the heart of a lion,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8460G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8460G\"></sup> will melt<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8460H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8460H\"></sup> with fear, for all Israel knows that your father is a fighter and that those with him are brave.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8460I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8460I\"></sup>",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>“So I advise you: Let all Israel, from Dan to Beersheba<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8461J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8461J\"></sup>—as numerous as the sand<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8461K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8461K\"></sup> on the seashore—be gathered to you, with you yourself leading them into battle.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Then we will attack him wherever he may be found, and we will fall on him as dew settles on the ground. Neither he nor any of his men will be left alive.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>If he withdraws into a city, then all Israel will bring ropes to that city, and we will drag it down to the valley<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8463L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8463L\"></sup> until not so much as a pebble is left.”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Absalom and all the men of Israel said, “The advice<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8464M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8464M\"></sup> of Hushai the Arkite is better than that of Ahithophel.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8464N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8464N\"></sup> For the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had determined to frustrate<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8464O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8464O\"></sup> the good advice of Ahithophel in order to bring disaster<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8464P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8464P\"></sup> on Absalom.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8464Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8464Q\"></sup>",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Hushai told Zadok and Abiathar, the priests, “Ahithophel has advised Absalom and the elders of Israel to do such and such, but I have advised them to do so and so.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Now send a message at once and tell David, ‘Do not spend the night at the fords in the wilderness;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8466R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8466R\"></sup> cross over without fail, or the king and all the people with him will be swallowed up.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8466S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8466S\"></sup>’”",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Jonathan<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8467T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8467T\"></sup> and Ahimaaz were staying at En Rogel.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8467U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8467U\"></sup> A female servant was to go and inform them, and they were to go and tell King David, for they could not risk being seen entering the city.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>But a young man saw them and told Absalom. So the two of them left at once and went to the house of a man in Bahurim.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8468V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8468V\"></sup> He had a well in his courtyard, and they climbed down into it.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>His wife took a covering and spread it out over the opening of the well and scattered grain over it. No one knew anything about it.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8469W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8469W\"></sup>",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>When Absalom’s men came to the woman<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8470X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8470X\"></sup> at the house, they asked, “Where are Ahimaaz and Jonathan?”The woman answered them, “They crossed over the brook.” The men searched but found no one, so they returned to Jerusalem.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>After they had gone, the two climbed out of the well and went to inform King David. They said to him, “Set out and cross the river at once; Ahithophel has advised such and such against you.”",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>So David and all the people with him set out and crossed the Jordan. By daybreak, no one was left who had not crossed the Jordan.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>When Ahithophel saw that his advice<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8473Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8473Y\"></sup> had not been followed, he saddled his donkey and set out for his house in his hometown. He put his house in order<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8473Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8473Z\"></sup> and then hanged himself. So he died and was buried in his father’s tomb.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>David went to Mahanaim,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8474AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8474AA\"></sup> and Absalom crossed the Jordan with all the men of Israel.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Absalom had appointed Amasa<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8475AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8475AB\"></sup> over the army in place of Joab. Amasa was the son of Jether,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8475AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8475AC\"></sup> an Ishmaelite who had married Abigail, the daughter of Nahash and sister of Zeruiah the mother of Joab.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>The Israelites and Absalom camped in the land of Gilead.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>When David came to Mahanaim, Shobi son of Nahash<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8477AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8477AD\"></sup> from Rabbah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8477AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8477AE\"></sup> of the Ammonites, and Makir<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8477AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8477AF\"></sup> son of Ammiel from Lo Debar, and Barzillai<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8477AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8477AG\"></sup> the Gileadite<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8477AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8477AH\"></sup> from Rogelim",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>brought bedding and bowls and articles of pottery. They also brought wheat and barley, flour and roasted grain, beans and lentils,",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>honey and curds, sheep, and cheese from cows’ milk for David and his people to eat.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8479AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8479AI\"></sup> For they said, “The people have become exhausted and hungry and thirsty in the wilderness.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8479AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8479AJ\"></sup>”"
		},
		"18": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">18 </span>David mustered the men who were with him and appointed over them commanders of thousands and commanders of hundreds.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>David sent out his troops,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8481A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8481A\"></sup> a third under the command of Joab, a third under Joab’s brother Abishai<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8481B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8481B\"></sup> son of Zeruiah, and a third under Ittai<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8481C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8481C\"></sup> the Gittite. The king told the troops, “I myself will surely march out with you.”",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>But the men said, “You must not go out; if we are forced to flee, they won’t care about us. Even if half of us die, they won’t care; but you are worth ten<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8482D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8482D\"></sup> thousand of us. It would be better now for you to give us support from the city.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8482E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8482E\"></sup>",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>The king answered, “I will do whatever seems best to you.”So the king stood beside the gate while all his men marched out in units of hundreds and of thousands.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>The king commanded Joab, Abishai and Ittai, “Be gentle with the young man Absalom for my sake.” And all the troops heard the king giving orders concerning Absalom to each of the commanders.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>David’s army marched out of the city to fight Israel, and the battle took place in the forest<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8485F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8485F\"></sup> of Ephraim.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>There Israel’s troops were routed by David’s men, and the casualties that day were great—twenty thousand men.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>The battle spread out over the whole countryside, and the forest swallowed up more men that day than the sword.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Now Absalom happened to meet David’s men. He was riding his mule, and as the mule went under the thick branches of a large oak, Absalom’s hair<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8488G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8488G\"></sup> got caught in the tree. He was left hanging in midair, while the mule he was riding kept on going.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>When one of the men saw what had happened, he told Joab, “I just saw Absalom hanging in an oak tree.”",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Joab said to the man who had told him this, “What! You saw him? Why didn’t you strike<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8490H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8490H\"></sup> him to the ground right there? Then I would have had to give you ten shekels of silver and a warrior’s belt.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8490I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8490I\"></sup>”",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>But the man replied, “Even if a thousand shekels were weighed out into my hands, I would not lay a hand on the king’s son. In our hearing the king commanded you and Abishai and Ittai, ‘Protect the young man Absalom for my sake.’",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>And if I had put my life in jeopardy—and nothing is hidden from the king<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8492J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8492J\"></sup>—you would have kept your distance from me.”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Joab<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8493K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8493K\"></sup> said, “I’m not going to wait like this for you.” So he took three javelins in his hand and plunged them into Absalom’s heart while Absalom was still alive in the oak tree.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>And ten of Joab’s armor-bearers surrounded Absalom, struck him and killed him.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8494L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8494L\"></sup>",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Then Joab<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8495M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8495M\"></sup> sounded the trumpet, and the troops stopped pursuing Israel, for Joab halted them.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>They took Absalom, threw him into a big pit in the forest and piled up<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8496N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8496N\"></sup> a large heap of rocks<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8496O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8496O\"></sup> over him. Meanwhile, all the Israelites fled to their homes.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>During his lifetime Absalom had taken a pillar and erected it in the King’s Valley<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8497P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8497P\"></sup> as a monument<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8497Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8497Q\"></sup> to himself, for he thought, “I have no son<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8497R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8497R\"></sup> to carry on the memory of my name.” He named the pillar after himself, and it is called Absalom’s Monument to this day.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Now Ahimaaz<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8498S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8498S\"></sup> son of Zadok said, “Let me run and take the news to the king that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has vindicated him by delivering him from the hand of his enemies.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8498T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8498T\"></sup>”",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>“You are not the one to take the news today,” Joab told him. “You may take the news another time, but you must not do so today, because the king’s son is dead.”",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Then Joab said to a Cushite, “Go, tell the king what you have seen.” The Cushite bowed down before Joab and ran off.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Ahimaaz son of Zadok again said to Joab, “Come what may, please let me run behind the Cushite.”But Joab replied, “My son, why do you want to go? You don’t have any news that will bring you a reward.”",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>He said, “Come what may, I want to run.”So Joab said, “Run!” Then Ahimaaz ran by way of the plain and outran the Cushite.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>While David was sitting between the inner and outer gates, the watchman<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8503U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8503U\"></sup> went up to the roof of the gateway by the wall. As he looked out, he saw a man running alone.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>The watchman called out to the king and reported it.The king said, “If he is alone, he must have good news.” And the runner came closer and closer.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Then the watchman saw another runner, and he called down to the gatekeeper, “Look, another man running alone!”The king said, “He must be bringing good news,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8505V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8505V\"></sup> too.”",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>The watchman said, “It seems to me that the first one runs like<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8506W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8506W\"></sup> Ahimaaz son of Zadok.”“He’s a good man,” the king said. “He comes with good news.”",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Then Ahimaaz called out to the king, “All is well!” He bowed down before the king with his face to the ground and said, “Praise be to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God! He has delivered up those who lifted their hands against my lord the king.”",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>The king asked, “Is the young man Absalom safe?”Ahimaaz answered, “I saw great confusion just as Joab was about to send the king’s servant and me, your servant, but I don’t know what it was.”",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>The king said, “Stand aside and wait here.” So he stepped aside and stood there.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>Then the Cushite arrived and said, “My lord the king, hear the good news! The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has vindicated you today by delivering you from the hand of all who rose up against you.”",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>The king asked the Cushite, “Is the young man Absalom safe?”The Cushite replied, “May the enemies of my lord the king and all who rise up to harm you be like that young man.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8511X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8511X\"></sup>",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>The king was shaken. He went up to the room over the gateway and wept. As he went, he said: “O my son Absalom! My son, my son Absalom! If only I had died<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8512Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8512Y\"></sup> instead of you—O Absalom, my son, my son!”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8512Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8512Z\"></sup>"
		},
		"19": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">19 </span>Joab was told, “The king is weeping and mourning for Absalom.”",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>And for the whole army the victory that day was turned into mourning, because on that day the troops heard it said, “The king is grieving for his son.”",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>The men stole into the city that day as men steal in who are ashamed when they flee from battle.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>The king covered his face and cried aloud, “O my son Absalom! O Absalom, my son, my son!”",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Then Joab went into the house to the king and said, “Today you have humiliated all your men, who have just saved your life and the lives of your sons and daughters and the lives of your wives and concubines.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>You love those who hate you and hate those who love you. You have made it clear today that the commanders and their men mean nothing to you. I see that you would be pleased if Absalom were alive today and all of us were dead.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Now go out and encourage your men. I swear by the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> that if you don’t go out, not a man will be left with you by nightfall. This will be worse for you than all the calamities that have come on you from your youth till now.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8519A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8519A\"></sup>",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>So the king got up and took his seat in the gateway. When the men were told, “The king is sitting in the gateway,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8520B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8520B\"></sup>” they all came before him.Meanwhile, the Israelites had fled to their homes.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Throughout the tribes of Israel, all the people were arguing among themselves, saying, “The king delivered us from the hand of our enemies; he is the one who rescued us from the hand of the Philistines.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8521C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8521C\"></sup> But now he has fled the country to escape from Absalom;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8521D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8521D\"></sup>",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>and Absalom, whom we anointed to rule over us, has died in battle. So why do you say nothing about bringing the king back?”",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>King David sent this message to Zadok<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8523E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8523E\"></sup> and Abiathar, the priests: “Ask the elders of Judah, ‘Why should you be the last to bring the king back to his palace, since what is being said throughout Israel has reached the king at his quarters?",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>You are my relatives, my own flesh and blood. So why should you be the last to bring back the king?’",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>And say to Amasa,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8525F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8525F\"></sup> ‘Are you not my own flesh and blood?<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8525G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8525G\"></sup> May God deal with me, be it ever so severely,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8525H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8525H\"></sup> if you are not the commander of my army for life in place of Joab.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8525I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8525I\"></sup>’”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>He won over the hearts of the men of Judah so that they were all of one mind. They sent word to the king, “Return, you and all your men.”",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Then the king returned and went as far as the Jordan.Now the men of Judah had come to Gilgal<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8527J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8527J\"></sup> to go out and meet the king and bring him across the Jordan.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Shimei<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8528K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8528K\"></sup> son of Gera, the Benjamite from Bahurim, hurried down with the men of Judah to meet King David.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>With him were a thousand Benjamites, along with Ziba,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8529L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8529L\"></sup> the steward of Saul’s household,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8529M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8529M\"></sup> and his fifteen sons and twenty servants. They rushed to the Jordan, where the king was.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>They crossed at the ford to take the king’s household over and to do whatever he wished.When Shimei son of Gera crossed the Jordan, he fell prostrate before the king",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>and said to him, “May my lord not hold me guilty. Do not remember how your servant did wrong on the day my lord the king left Jerusalem.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8531N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8531N\"></sup> May the king put it out of his mind.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>For I your servant know that I have sinned, but today I have come here as the first from the tribes of Joseph to come down and meet my lord the king.”",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Then Abishai<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8533O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8533O\"></sup> son of Zeruiah said, “Shouldn’t Shimei be put to death for this? He cursed<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8533P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8533P\"></sup> the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>’s anointed.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8533Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8533Q\"></sup>",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>David replied, “What does this have to do with you, you sons of Zeruiah?<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8534R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8534R\"></sup> What right do you have to interfere? Should anyone be put to death in Israel today?<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8534S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8534S\"></sup> Don’t I know that today I am king over Israel?”",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>So the king said to Shimei, “You shall not die.” And the king promised him on oath.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8535T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8535T\"></sup>",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Mephibosheth,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8536U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8536U\"></sup> Saul’s grandson, also went down to meet the king. He had not taken care of his feet or trimmed his mustache or washed his clothes from the day the king left until the day he returned safely.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>When he came from Jerusalem to meet the king, the king asked him, “Why didn’t you go with me,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8537V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8537V\"></sup> Mephibosheth?”",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>He said, “My lord the king, since I your servant am lame,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8538W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8538W\"></sup> I said, ‘I will have my donkey saddled and will ride on it, so I can go with the king.’ But Ziba<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8538X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8538X\"></sup> my servant betrayed me.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>And he has slandered your servant to my lord the king. My lord the king is like an angel<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8539Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8539Y\"></sup> of God; so do whatever you wish.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>All my grandfather’s descendants deserved nothing but death<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8540Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8540Z\"></sup> from my lord the king, but you gave your servant a place among those who eat at your table.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8540AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8540AA\"></sup> So what right do I have to make any more appeals to the king?”",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>The king said to him, “Why say more? I order you and Ziba to divide the land.”",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>Mephibosheth said to the king, “Let him take everything, now that my lord the king has returned home safely.”",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>Barzillai<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8543AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8543AB\"></sup> the Gileadite also came down from Rogelim to cross the Jordan with the king and to send him on his way from there.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>Now Barzillai was very old, eighty years of age. He had provided for the king during his stay in Mahanaim, for he was a very wealthy<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8544AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8544AC\"></sup> man.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>The king said to Barzillai, “Cross over with me and stay with me in Jerusalem, and I will provide for you.”",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>But Barzillai answered the king, “How many more years will I live, that I should go up to Jerusalem with the king?",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>I am now eighty<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8547AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8547AD\"></sup> years old. Can I tell the difference between what is enjoyable and what is not? Can your servant taste what he eats and drinks? Can I still hear the voices of male and female singers?<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8547AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8547AE\"></sup> Why should your servant be an added<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8547AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8547AF\"></sup> burden to my lord the king?",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>Your servant will cross over the Jordan with the king for a short distance, but why should the king reward me in this way?",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>Let your servant return, that I may die in my own town near the tomb of my father<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8549AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8549AG\"></sup> and mother. But here is your servant Kimham.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8549AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8549AH\"></sup> Let him cross over with my lord the king. Do for him whatever you wish.”",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>The king said, “Kimham shall cross over with me, and I will do for him whatever you wish. And anything you desire from me I will do for you.”",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>So all the people crossed the Jordan, and then the king crossed over. The king kissed Barzillai and bid him farewell,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8551AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8551AI\"></sup> and Barzillai returned to his home.",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>When the king crossed over to Gilgal, Kimham crossed with him. All the troops of Judah and half the troops of Israel had taken the king over.",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>Soon all the men of Israel were coming to the king and saying to him, “Why did our brothers, the men of Judah, steal the king away and bring him and his household across the Jordan, together with all his men?”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8553AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8553AJ\"></sup>",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>All the men of Judah answered the men of Israel, “We did this because the king is closely related to us. Why are you angry about it? Have we eaten any of the king’s provisions? Have we taken anything for ourselves?”",
			"43": "<sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup>Then the men of Israel<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8555AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8555AK\"></sup> answered the men of Judah, “We have ten shares in the king; so we have a greater claim on David than you have. Why then do you treat us with contempt? Weren’t we the first to speak of bringing back our king?”But the men of Judah pressed their claims even more forcefully than the men of Israel."
		},
		"20": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">20 </span>Now a troublemaker named Sheba son of Bikri, a Benjamite, happened to be there. He sounded the trumpet and shouted,“We have no share<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8556A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8556A\"></sup> in David,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8556B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8556B\"></sup>no part in Jesse’s son!<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8556C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8556C\"></sup>Every man to his tent, Israel!”",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>So all the men of Israel deserted David to follow Sheba son of Bikri. But the men of Judah stayed by their king all the way from the Jordan to Jerusalem.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>When David returned to his palace in Jerusalem, he took the ten concubines<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8558D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8558D\"></sup> he had left to take care of the palace and put them in a house under guard. He provided for them but had no sexual relations with them. They were kept in confinement till the day of their death, living as widows.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Then the king said to Amasa,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8559E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8559E\"></sup> “Summon the men of Judah to come to me within three days, and be here yourself.”",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>But when Amasa went to summon Judah, he took longer than the time the king had set for him.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>David said to Abishai,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8561F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8561F\"></sup> “Now Sheba son of Bikri will do us more harm than Absalom did. Take your master’s men and pursue him, or he will find fortified cities and escape from us.”",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>So Joab’s men and the Kerethites<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8562G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8562G\"></sup> and Pelethites and all the mighty warriors went out under the command of Abishai. They marched out from Jerusalem to pursue Sheba son of Bikri.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>While they were at the great rock in Gibeon,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8563H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8563H\"></sup> Amasa came to meet them. Joab<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8563I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8563I\"></sup> was wearing his military tunic, and strapped over it at his waist was a belt with a dagger in its sheath. As he stepped forward, it dropped out of its sheath.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Joab said to Amasa, “How are you, my brother?” Then Joab took Amasa by the beard with his right hand to kiss him.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Amasa was not on his guard against the dagger<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8565J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8565J\"></sup> in Joab’s<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8565K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8565K\"></sup> hand, and Joab plunged it into his belly, and his intestines spilled out on the ground. Without being stabbed again, Amasa died. Then Joab and his brother Abishai pursued Sheba son of Bikri.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>One of Joab’s men stood beside Amasa and said, “Whoever favors Joab, and whoever is for David, let him follow Joab!”",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Amasa lay wallowing in his blood in the middle of the road, and the man saw that all the troops came to a halt<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8567L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8567L\"></sup> there. When he realized that everyone who came up to Amasa stopped, he dragged him from the road into a field and threw a garment over him.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>After Amasa had been removed from the road, everyone went on with Joab to pursue Sheba son of Bikri.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Sheba passed through all the tribes of Israel to Abel Beth Maakah and through the entire region of the Bikrites,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8569M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8569M\"></sup> who gathered together and followed him.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>All the troops with Joab came and besieged Sheba in Abel Beth Maakah.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8570N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8570N\"></sup> They built a siege ramp<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8570O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8570O\"></sup> up to the city, and it stood against the outer fortifications. While they were battering the wall to bring it down,",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>a wise woman<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8571P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8571P\"></sup> called from the city, “Listen! Listen! Tell Joab to come here so I can speak to him.”",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>He went toward her, and she asked, “Are you Joab?”“I am,” he answered.She said, “Listen to what your servant has to say.”“I’m listening,” he said.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>She continued, “Long ago they used to say, ‘Get your answer at Abel,’ and that settled it.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>We are the peaceful<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8574Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8574Q\"></sup> and faithful in Israel. You are trying to destroy a city that is a mother in Israel. Why do you want to swallow up the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>’s inheritance?”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8574R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8574R\"></sup>",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>“Far be it from me!” Joab replied, “Far be it from me to swallow up or destroy!",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>That is not the case. A man named Sheba son of Bikri, from the hill country of Ephraim, has lifted up his hand against the king, against David. Hand over this one man, and I’ll withdraw from the city.”The woman said to Joab, “His head<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8576S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8576S\"></sup> will be thrown to you from the wall.”",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Then the woman went to all the people with her wise advice,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8577T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8577T\"></sup> and they cut off the head of Sheba son of Bikri and threw it to Joab. So he sounded the trumpet, and his men dispersed from the city, each returning to his home. And Joab went back to the king in Jerusalem.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Joab<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8578U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8578U\"></sup> was over Israel’s entire army; Benaiah son of Jehoiada was over the Kerethites and Pelethites;",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Adoniram<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8579V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8579V\"></sup> was in charge of forced labor; Jehoshaphat<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8579W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8579W\"></sup> son of Ahilud was recorder;",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Sheva was secretary; Zadok<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8580X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8580X\"></sup> and Abiathar were priests;",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>and Ira the Jairite was David’s priest."
		},
		"21": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">21 </span>During the reign of David, there was a famine<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8582A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8582A\"></sup> for three successive years; so David sought<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8582B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8582B\"></sup> the face of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>. The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said, “It is on account of Saul and his blood-stained house; it is because he put the Gibeonites to death.”",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>The king summoned the Gibeonites<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8583C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8583C\"></sup> and spoke to them. (Now the Gibeonites were not a part of Israel but were survivors of the Amorites; the Israelites had sworn to spare them, but Saul in his zeal for Israel and Judah had tried to annihilate them.)",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>David asked the Gibeonites, “What shall I do for you? How shall I make atonement so that you will bless the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>’s inheritance?”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8584D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8584D\"></sup>",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>The Gibeonites answered him, “We have no right to demand silver or gold from Saul or his family, nor do we have the right to put anyone in Israel to death.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8585E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8585E\"></sup>“What do you want me to do for you?” David asked.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>They answered the king, “As for the man who destroyed us and plotted against us so that we have been decimated and have no place anywhere in Israel,",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>let seven of his male descendants be given to us to be killed and their bodies exposed<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8587F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8587F\"></sup> before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> at Gibeah of Saul—the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>’s chosen<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8587G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8587G\"></sup> one.”So the king said, “I will give them to you.”",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>The king spared Mephibosheth<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8588H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8588H\"></sup> son of Jonathan, the son of Saul, because of the oath<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8588I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8588I\"></sup> before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> between David and Jonathan son of Saul.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>But the king took Armoni and Mephibosheth, the two sons of Aiah’s daughter Rizpah,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8589J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8589J\"></sup> whom she had borne to Saul, together with the five sons of Saul’s daughter Merab, whom she had borne to Adriel son of Barzillai the Meholathite.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8589K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8589K\"></sup>",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>He handed them over to the Gibeonites, who killed them and exposed their bodies on a hill before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>. All seven of them fell together; they were put to death<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8590L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8590L\"></sup> during the first days of the harvest, just as the barley harvest was beginning.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8590M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8590M\"></sup>",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Rizpah daughter of Aiah took sackcloth and spread it out for herself on a rock. From the beginning of the harvest till the rain poured down from the heavens on the bodies, she did not let the birds touch them by day or the wild animals by night.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8591N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8591N\"></sup>",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>When David was told what Aiah’s daughter Rizpah, Saul’s concubine, had done,",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>he went and took the bones of Saul<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8593O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8593O\"></sup> and his son Jonathan from the citizens of Jabesh Gilead.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8593P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8593P\"></sup> (They had stolen their bodies from the public square at Beth Shan,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8593Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8593Q\"></sup> where the Philistines had hung<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8593R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8593R\"></sup> them after they struck Saul down on Gilboa.)<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8593S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8593S\"></sup>",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>David brought the bones of Saul and his son Jonathan from there, and the bones of those who had been killed and exposed were gathered up.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>They buried the bones of Saul and his son Jonathan in the tomb of Saul’s father Kish, at Zela<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8595T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8595T\"></sup> in Benjamin, and did everything the king commanded. After that,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8595U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8595U\"></sup> God answered prayer<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8595V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8595V\"></sup> in behalf of the land.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8595W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8595W\"></sup>",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Once again there was a battle between the Philistines<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8596Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8596Y\"></sup> and Israel. David went down with his men to fight against the Philistines, and he became exhausted.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>And Ishbi-Benob, one of the descendants of Rapha, whose bronze spearhead weighed three hundred shekels and who was armed with a new sword, said he would kill David.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>But Abishai<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8598Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8598Z\"></sup> son of Zeruiah came to David’s rescue; he struck the Philistine down and killed him. Then David’s men swore to him, saying, “Never again will you go out with us to battle, so that the lamp<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8598AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8598AA\"></sup> of Israel will not be extinguished.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8598AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8598AB\"></sup>”",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>In the course of time, there was another battle with the Philistines, at Gob. At that time Sibbekai<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8599AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8599AC\"></sup> the Hushathite killed Saph, one of the descendants of Rapha.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>In another battle with the Philistines at Gob, Elhanan son of Jair the Bethlehemite killed the brother of Goliath the Gittite,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8600AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8600AD\"></sup> who had a spear with a shaft like a weaver’s rod.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8600AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8600AE\"></sup>",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>In still another battle, which took place at Gath, there was a huge man with six fingers on each hand and six toes on each foot—twenty-four in all. He also was descended from Rapha.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>When he taunted<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8602AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8602AF\"></sup> Israel, Jonathan son of Shimeah,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8602AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8602AG\"></sup> David’s brother, killed him.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>These four were descendants of Rapha in Gath, and they fell at the hands of David and his men."
		},
		"22": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">22 </span>David sang<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8604B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8604B\"></sup> to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> the words of this song when the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> delivered him from the hand of all his enemies and from the hand of Saul.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>He said:“The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> is my rock,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8605C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8605C\"></sup> my fortress<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8605D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8605D\"></sup> and my deliverer;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8605E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8605E\"></sup>",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup><span class=\"indent-1-breaks\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span>my God is my rock, in whom I take refuge,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8606F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8606F\"></sup>my shield<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8606G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8606G\"></sup> and the horn<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8606H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8606H\"></sup> of my salvation.He is my stronghold,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8606I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8606I\"></sup> my refuge and my savior—from violent people you save me.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>“I called to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, who is worthy<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8607J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8607J\"></sup> of praise,and have been saved from my enemies.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>The waves<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8608K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8608K\"></sup> of death swirled about me;the torrents of destruction overwhelmed me.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>The cords of the grave<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8609L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8609L\"></sup> coiled around me;the snares of death confronted me.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>“In my distress<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8610M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8610M\"></sup> I called<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8610N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8610N\"></sup> to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>;I called out to my God.From his temple he heard my voice;my cry came to his ears.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>The earth<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8611O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8611O\"></sup> trembled and quaked,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8611P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8611P\"></sup>the foundations<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8611Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8611Q\"></sup> of the heavens shook;they trembled because he was angry.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Smoke rose from his nostrils;consuming fire<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8612R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8612R\"></sup> came from his mouth,burning coals<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8612S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8612S\"></sup> blazed out of it.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>He parted the heavens and came down;dark clouds<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8613T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8613T\"></sup> were under his feet.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>He mounted the cherubim<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8614U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8614U\"></sup> and flew;he soared on the wings of the wind.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8614V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8614V\"></sup>",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>He made darkness<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8615W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8615W\"></sup> his canopy around him—the dark rain clouds of the sky.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Out of the brightness of his presencebolts of lightning<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8616X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8616X\"></sup> blazed forth.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> thundered<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8617Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8617Y\"></sup> from heaven;the voice of the Most High resounded.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>He shot his arrows<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8618Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8618Z\"></sup> and scattered the enemy,with great bolts of lightning he routed them.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>The valleys of the sea were exposedand the foundations of the earth laid bareat the rebuke<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8619AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8619AA\"></sup> of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>,at the blast<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8619AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8619AB\"></sup> of breath from his nostrils.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>“He reached down from on high<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8620AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8620AC\"></sup> and took hold of me;he drew<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8620AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8620AD\"></sup> me out of deep waters.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>He rescued<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8621AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8621AE\"></sup> me from my powerful enemy,from my foes, who were too strong for me.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>They confronted me in the day of my disaster,but the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> was my support.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8622AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8622AF\"></sup>",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>He brought me out into a spacious<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8623AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8623AG\"></sup> place;he rescued<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8623AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8623AH\"></sup> me because he delighted<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8623AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8623AI\"></sup> in me.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8623AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8623AJ\"></sup>",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>“The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has dealt with me according to my righteousness;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8624AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8624AK\"></sup>according to the cleanness<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8624AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8624AL\"></sup> of my hands<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8624AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8624AM\"></sup> he has rewarded me.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>For I have kept<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8625AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8625AN\"></sup> the ways of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>;I am not guilty of turning from my God.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>All his laws are before me;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8626AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8626AO\"></sup>I have not turned<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8626AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8626AP\"></sup> away from his decrees.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>I have been blameless<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8627AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8627AQ\"></sup> before himand have kept myself from sin.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has rewarded me according to my righteousness,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8628AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8628AR\"></sup>according to my cleanness in his sight.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>“To the faithful you show yourself faithful,to the blameless you show yourself blameless,",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>to the pure<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8630AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8630AS\"></sup> you show yourself pure,but to the devious you show yourself shrewd.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8630AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8630AT\"></sup>",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>You save the humble,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8631AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8631AU\"></sup>but your eyes are on the haughty<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8631AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8631AV\"></sup> to bring them low.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8631AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8631AW\"></sup>",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>You, <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, are my lamp;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8632AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8632AX\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> turns my darkness into light.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>With your help I can advance against a troop;with my God I can scale a wall.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>“As for God, his way is perfect:<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8634AY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AY&quot;&gt;AY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8634AY\"></sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>’s word is flawless;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8634AZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AZ&quot;&gt;AZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8634AZ\"></sup>he shields<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8634BA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BA&quot;&gt;BA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8634BA\"></sup> all who take refuge in him.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>For who is God besides the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>?And who is the Rock<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8635BB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BB&quot;&gt;BB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8635BB\"></sup> except our God?<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8635BC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BC&quot;&gt;BC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8635BC\"></sup>",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>It is God who arms me with strengthand keeps my way secure.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>He makes my feet like the feet of a deer;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8637BD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BD&quot;&gt;BD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8637BD\"></sup>he causes me to stand on the heights.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8637BE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BE&quot;&gt;BE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8637BE\"></sup>",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>He trains my hands<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8638BF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BF&quot;&gt;BF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8638BF\"></sup> for battle;my arms can bend a bow<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8638BG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BG&quot;&gt;BG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8638BG\"></sup> of bronze.",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>You make your saving help my shield;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8639BH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BH&quot;&gt;BH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8639BH\"></sup>your help has made me great.",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>You provide a broad path<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8640BI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BI&quot;&gt;BI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8640BI\"></sup> for my feet,so that my ankles do not give way.",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>“I pursued my enemies and crushed them;I did not turn back till they were destroyed.",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>I crushed<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8642BJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BJ&quot;&gt;BJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8642BJ\"></sup> them completely, and they could not rise;they fell beneath my feet.",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>You armed me with strength for battle;you humbled my adversaries before me.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8643BK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BK&quot;&gt;BK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8643BK\"></sup>",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>You made my enemies turn their backs<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8644BL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BL&quot;&gt;BL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8644BL\"></sup> in flight,and I destroyed my foes.",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>They cried for help,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8645BM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BM&quot;&gt;BM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8645BM\"></sup> but there was no one to save them—<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8645BN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BN&quot;&gt;BN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8645BN\"></sup>to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, but he did not answer.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8645BO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BO&quot;&gt;BO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8645BO\"></sup>",
			"43": "<sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup>I beat them as fine as the dust<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8646BP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BP&quot;&gt;BP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8646BP\"></sup> of the earth;I pounded and trampled<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8646BQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BQ&quot;&gt;BQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8646BQ\"></sup> them like mud<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8646BR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BR&quot;&gt;BR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8646BR\"></sup> in the streets.",
			"44": "<sup class=\"versenum\">44 </sup>“You have delivered<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8647BS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BS&quot;&gt;BS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8647BS\"></sup> me from the attacks of the peoples;you have preserved<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8647BT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BT&quot;&gt;BT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8647BT\"></sup> me as the head of nations.People<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8647BU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BU&quot;&gt;BU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8647BU\"></sup> I did not know now serve me,",
			"45": "<sup class=\"versenum\">45 </sup><span class=\"indent-1-breaks\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span>foreigners cower<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8648BV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BV&quot;&gt;BV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8648BV\"></sup> before me;as soon as they hear of me, they obey me.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8648BW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BW&quot;&gt;BW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8648BW\"></sup>",
			"46": "<sup class=\"versenum\">46 </sup>They all lose heart;they come trembling<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8649BX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BX&quot;&gt;BX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8649BX\"></sup> from their strongholds.",
			"47": "<sup class=\"versenum\">47 </sup>“The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> lives! Praise be to my Rock!Exalted<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8650BY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BY&quot;&gt;BY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8650BY\"></sup> be my God, the Rock, my Savior!<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8650BZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BZ&quot;&gt;BZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8650BZ\"></sup>",
			"48": "<sup class=\"versenum\">48 </sup>He is the God who avenges<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8651CA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CA&quot;&gt;CA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8651CA\"></sup> me,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8651CB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CB&quot;&gt;CB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8651CB\"></sup>who puts the nations under me,",
			"49": "<sup class=\"versenum\">49 </sup><span class=\"indent-1-breaks\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span>who sets me free from my enemies.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8652CC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CC&quot;&gt;CC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8652CC\"></sup>You exalted me<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8652CD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CD&quot;&gt;CD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8652CD\"></sup> above my foes;from a violent man you rescued me.",
			"50": "<sup class=\"versenum\">50 </sup>Therefore I will praise you, <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, among the nations;I will sing the praises<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8653CE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CE&quot;&gt;CE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8653CE\"></sup> of your name.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8653CF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CF&quot;&gt;CF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8653CF\"></sup>",
			"51": "<sup class=\"versenum\">51 </sup>“He gives his king great victories;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8654CG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CG&quot;&gt;CG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8654CG\"></sup>he shows unfailing kindness to his anointed,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8654CH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CH&quot;&gt;CH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8654CH\"></sup>to David<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8654CI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CI&quot;&gt;CI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8654CI\"></sup> and his descendants forever.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8654CJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CJ&quot;&gt;CJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8654CJ\"></sup>"
		},
		"23": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">23 </span>These are the last words of David:“The inspired utterance of David son of Jesse,the utterance of the man exalted<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8655A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8655A\"></sup> by the Most High,the man anointed<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8655B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8655B\"></sup> by the God of Jacob,the hero of Israel’s songs:",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>“The Spirit<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8656C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8656C\"></sup> of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> spoke through me;his word was on my tongue.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>The God of Israel spoke,the Rock<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8657D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8657D\"></sup> of Israel said to me:‘When one rules over people in righteousness,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8657E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8657E\"></sup>when he rules in the fear<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8657F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8657F\"></sup> of God,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8657G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8657G\"></sup>",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>he is like the light<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8658H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8658H\"></sup> of morning<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8658I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8658I\"></sup> at sunrise<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8658J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8658J\"></sup>on a cloudless morning,like the brightness after rain<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8658K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8658K\"></sup>that brings grass from the earth.’",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>“If my house were not right with God,surely he would not have made with me an everlasting covenant,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8659L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8659L\"></sup>arranged and secured in every part;surely he would not bring to fruition my salvationand grant me my every desire.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>But evil men are all to be cast aside like thorns,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8660M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8660M\"></sup>which are not gathered with the hand.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Whoever touches thornsuses a tool of iron or the shaft of a spear;they are burned up where they lie.”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>These are the names of David’s mighty warriors:<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8662O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8662O\"></sup>Josheb-Basshebeth,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8662P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8662P\"></sup> a Tahkemonite, was chief of the Three; he raised his spear against eight hundred men, whom he killed in one encounter.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Next to him was Eleazar son of Dodai<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8663Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8663Q\"></sup> the Ahohite.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8663R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8663R\"></sup> As one of the three mighty warriors, he was with David when they taunted the Philistines gathered at Pas Dammim for battle. Then the Israelites retreated,",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>but Eleazar stood his ground and struck down the Philistines till his hand grew tired and froze to the sword. The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> brought about a great victory that day. The troops returned to Eleazar, but only to strip the dead.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Next to him was Shammah son of Agee the Hararite. When the Philistines banded together at a place where there was a field full of lentils, Israel’s troops fled from them.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>But Shammah took his stand in the middle of the field. He defended it and struck the Philistines down, and the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> brought about a great victory.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>During harvest time, three of the thirty chief warriors came down to David at the cave of Adullam,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8667S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8667S\"></sup> while a band of Philistines was encamped in the Valley of Rephaim.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8667T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8667T\"></sup>",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>At that time David was in the stronghold,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8668U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8668U\"></sup> and the Philistine garrison was at Bethlehem.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8668V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8668V\"></sup>",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>David longed for water and said, “Oh, that someone would get me a drink of water from the well near the gate of Bethlehem!”",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>So the three mighty warriors broke through the Philistine lines, drew water from the well near the gate of Bethlehem and carried it back to David. But he refused to drink it; instead, he poured<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8670W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8670W\"></sup> it out before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>“Far be it from me, <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, to do this!” he said. “Is it not the blood<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8671X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8671X\"></sup> of men who went at the risk of their lives?” And David would not drink it.Such were the exploits of the three mighty warriors.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Abishai<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8672Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8672Y\"></sup> the brother of Joab son of Zeruiah was chief of the Three. He raised his spear against three hundred men, whom he killed, and so he became as famous as the Three.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Was he not held in greater honor than the Three? He became their commander, even though he was not included among them.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Benaiah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8674Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8674Z\"></sup> son of Jehoiada, a valiant fighter from Kabzeel,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8674AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8674AA\"></sup> performed great exploits. He struck down Moab’s two mightiest warriors. He also went down into a pit on a snowy day and killed a lion.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>And he struck down a huge Egyptian. Although the Egyptian had a spear in his hand, Benaiah went against him with a club. He snatched the spear from the Egyptian’s hand and killed him with his own spear.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Such were the exploits of Benaiah son of Jehoiada; he too was as famous as the three mighty warriors.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>He was held in greater honor than any of the Thirty, but he was not included among the Three. And David put him in charge of his bodyguard.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Among the Thirty were:Asahel<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8678AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8678AB\"></sup> the brother of Joab,Elhanan son of Dodo from Bethlehem,",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Shammah the Harodite,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8679AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8679AC\"></sup>Elika the Harodite,",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Helez<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8680AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8680AD\"></sup> the Paltite,Ira<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8680AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8680AE\"></sup> son of Ikkesh from Tekoa,",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Abiezer<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8681AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8681AF\"></sup> from Anathoth,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8681AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8681AG\"></sup>Sibbekai the Hushathite,",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Zalmon the Ahohite,Maharai<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8682AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8682AH\"></sup> the Netophathite,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8682AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8682AI\"></sup>",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>Heled<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8683AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8683AJ\"></sup> son of Baanah the Netophathite,Ithai son of Ribai from Gibeah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8683AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8683AK\"></sup> in Benjamin,",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>Benaiah the Pirathonite,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8684AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8684AL\"></sup>Hiddai from the ravines of Gaash,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8684AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8684AM\"></sup>",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>Abi-Albon the Arbathite,Azmaveth the Barhumite,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8685AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8685AN\"></sup>",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>Eliahba the Shaalbonite,the sons of Jashen,Jonathan",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>son of Shammah the Hararite,Ahiam son of Sharar the Hararite,",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>Eliphelet son of Ahasbai the Maakathite,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8688AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8688AO\"></sup>Eliam<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8688AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8688AP\"></sup> son of Ahithophel<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8688AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8688AQ\"></sup> the Gilonite,",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>Hezro the Carmelite,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8689AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8689AR\"></sup>Paarai the Arbite,",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>Igal son of Nathan from Zobah,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8690AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8690AS\"></sup>the son of Hagri,",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>Zelek the Ammonite,Naharai the Beerothite,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8691AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8691AT\"></sup> the armor-bearer of Joab son of Zeruiah,",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>Ira the Ithrite,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8692AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8692AU\"></sup>Gareb the Ithrite",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>and Uriah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8693AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8693AV\"></sup> the Hittite.There were thirty-seven in all."
		},
		"24": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">24 </span>Again<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8694B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8694B\"></sup> the anger of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> burned against Israel,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8694C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8694C\"></sup> and he incited David against them, saying, “Go and take a census of<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8694D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8694D\"></sup> Israel and Judah.”",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>So the king said to Joab<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8695E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8695E\"></sup> and the army commanders with him, “Go throughout the tribes of Israel from Dan to Beersheba<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8695F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8695F\"></sup> and enroll<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8695G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8695G\"></sup> the fighting men, so that I may know how many there are.”",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>But Joab<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8696H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8696H\"></sup> replied to the king, “May the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God multiply the troops a hundred times over,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8696I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8696I\"></sup> and may the eyes of my lord the king see it. But why does my lord the king want to do such a thing?”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>The king’s word, however, overruled Joab and the army commanders; so they left the presence of the king to enroll the fighting men of Israel.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>After crossing the Jordan, they camped near Aroer,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8698J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8698J\"></sup> south of the town in the gorge, and then went through Gad and on to Jazer.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8698K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8698K\"></sup>",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>They went to Gilead and the region of Tahtim Hodshi, and on to Dan Jaan and around toward Sidon.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8699L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8699L\"></sup>",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Then they went toward the fortress of Tyre<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8700M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8700M\"></sup> and all the towns of the Hivites<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8700N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8700N\"></sup> and Canaanites. Finally, they went on to Beersheba<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8700O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8700O\"></sup> in the Negev<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8700P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8700P\"></sup> of Judah.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>After they had gone through the entire land, they came back to Jerusalem at the end of nine months and twenty days.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Joab reported the number of the fighting men to the king: In Israel there were eight hundred thousand able-bodied men who could handle a sword, and in Judah five hundred thousand.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8702Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8702Q\"></sup>",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>David was conscience-stricken<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8703R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8703R\"></sup> after he had counted the fighting men, and he said to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, “I have sinned<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8703S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8703S\"></sup> greatly in what I have done. Now, <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, I beg you, take away the guilt of your servant. I have done a very foolish thing.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8703T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8703T\"></sup>”",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Before David got up the next morning, the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had come to Gad<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8704U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8704U\"></sup> the prophet, David’s seer:<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8704V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8704V\"></sup>",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>“Go and tell David, ‘This is what the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> says: I am giving you three options. Choose one of them for me to carry out against you.’”",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>So Gad went to David and said to him, “Shall there come on you three years of famine<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8706W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8706W\"></sup> in your land? Or three months of fleeing from your enemies while they pursue you? Or three days of plague<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8706X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8706X\"></sup> in your land? Now then, think it over and decide how I should answer the one who sent me.”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>David said to Gad, “I am in deep distress. Let us fall into the hands of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, for his mercy<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8707Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8707Y\"></sup> is great; but do not let me fall into human hands.”",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>So the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> sent a plague on Israel from that morning until the end of the time designated, and seventy thousand of the people from Dan to Beersheba died.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8708Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8708Z\"></sup>",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>When the angel stretched out his hand to destroy Jerusalem, the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> relented<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8709AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8709AA\"></sup> concerning the disaster and said to the angel who was afflicting the people, “Enough! Withdraw your hand.” The angel of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8709AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8709AB\"></sup> was then at the threshing floor of Araunah the Jebusite.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>When David saw the angel who was striking down the people, he said to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, “I have sinned; I, the shepherd, have done wrong. These are but sheep.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8710AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8710AC\"></sup> What have they done?<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8710AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8710AD\"></sup> Let your hand fall on me and my family.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8710AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8710AE\"></sup>",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>On that day Gad went to David and said to him, “Go up and build an altar to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> on the threshing floor of Araunah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8711AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8711AG\"></sup> the Jebusite.”",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>So David went up, as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had commanded through Gad.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>When Araunah looked and saw the king and his officials coming toward him, he went out and bowed down before the king with his face to the ground.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Araunah said, “Why has my lord the king come to his servant?”“To buy your threshing floor,” David answered, “so I can build an altar to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, that the plague on the people may be stopped.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8714AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8714AH\"></sup>",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Araunah said to David, “Let my lord the king take whatever he wishes and offer it up. Here are oxen<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8715AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8715AI\"></sup> for the burnt offering, and here are threshing sledges and ox yokes for the wood.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Your Majesty, Araunah gives<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8716AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8716AJ\"></sup> all this to the king.” Araunah also said to him, “May the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God accept you.”",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>But the king replied to Araunah, “No, I insist on paying you for it. I will not sacrifice to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> my God burnt offerings that cost me nothing.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8717AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8717AK\"></sup>So David bought the threshing floor and the oxen and paid fifty shekels<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8717AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8717AL\"></sup> of silver for them.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>David built an altar<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8718AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8718AM\"></sup> to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> there and sacrificed burnt offerings and fellowship offerings. Then the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> answered his prayer<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8718AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8718AN\"></sup> in behalf of the land, and the plague on Israel was stopped."
		}
	}
};
module.exports = book;